1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,749
PREVIOUSLY

2
00:00:15,815 --> 00:00:17,717
Please welcome
Ryu Hyun-jin and Choo Shin-soo!

3
00:00:17,784 --> 00:00:19,219
As a year-end special,

4
00:00:19,285 --> 00:00:21,221
we plan to hold a championship.

5
00:00:21,287 --> 00:00:23,990
-Let's find out the current ranking.
-Only the top five chefs get to move on.

6
00:00:24,057 --> 00:00:25,492
I can win despite my lowest winning rate.

7
00:00:25,558 --> 00:00:27,494
Sung-jun, Stop Pigging Out.

8
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:28,628
Let's go!

9
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:30,797
This is nothing
compared to Hyun-jin's pain.

10
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:32,032
CHEF YOON NAM-NO

11
00:00:32,098 --> 00:00:33,700
KWON SUNG-JUN FAILS TO MOVE ON

12
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:36,169
If Poong wins, Eun-yeong is eliminated,

13
00:00:36,236 --> 00:00:37,771
-and Nam-no will move on.
-Yes!

14
00:00:37,837 --> 00:00:39,139
-I can do this.
-Please.

15
00:00:39,205 --> 00:00:40,907
Don't worry. I'll let you move up.

16
00:00:40,974 --> 00:00:42,308
Doesn't it have too much water?

17
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:43,643
It's a melon fritter.

18
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:45,478
It must be good.

19
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:47,380
I CAN'T BACK DOWN LIKE THIS!

20
00:00:47,447 --> 00:00:49,382
SHE MAKES
THE MOST DELICIOUS DEEP-FRIED DISH

21
00:00:49,449 --> 00:00:50,750
It's so good.

22
00:00:50,817 --> 00:00:52,118
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG

23
00:00:52,185 --> 00:00:54,154
Kim Poong, Strikeout!

24
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:55,955
<i>Nam-no does not make the cut.</i>

25
00:00:56,022 --> 00:00:59,259
<i>The chefs for the championship</i>
<i>have been decided.</i>

26
00:00:59,325 --> 00:01:01,394
HOW WILL THE REGULAR SEASON END?

27
00:01:01,461 --> 00:01:06,332
We're with world-renowned baseball stars,
Ryu Hyun-jin and Choo Shin-soo.

28
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:08,735
The two have known each other
for a very long time.

29
00:01:08,802 --> 00:01:10,770
<i>Back in 2009 and 2010,</i>

30
00:01:10,837 --> 00:01:14,541
I believe you two
were both on the national team.

31
00:01:14,607 --> 00:01:17,177
Shin-soo started his career
five years before Hyun-jin.

32
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:18,645
-Right?
-Yes, that's right.

33
00:01:18,711 --> 00:01:21,548
-But you always did Hyun-jin's laundry.
-What?

34
00:01:21,614 --> 00:01:22,816
That's the rumor going around.

35
00:01:22,882 --> 00:01:24,551
Should I talk first?

36
00:01:25,718 --> 00:01:27,520
I mean, that's the rumor.

37
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:28,788
Well, Hyun-jin was the best

38
00:01:28,855 --> 00:01:32,158
-whenever we played international games.
-I see.

39
00:01:32,225 --> 00:01:34,160
The result was important,

40
00:01:34,227 --> 00:01:35,495
so I did his laundry

41
00:01:35,562 --> 00:01:40,066
to help him stay in his best condition,
although he was my junior.

42
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:43,503
After we won and returned to our lodging,

43
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:46,406
that's when I treated him
as a junior player again.

44
00:01:46,473 --> 00:01:48,441
-You were done.
-Yes, you've won.

45
00:01:48,508 --> 00:01:50,977
I threw all my dirty clothes at him
and told him to wash them.

46
00:01:51,044 --> 00:01:52,745
YOU'RE ON LAUNDRY DUTY FROM NOW ON

47
00:01:52,812 --> 00:01:55,148
This never happens
in the world of soccer, does it?

48
00:01:55,215 --> 00:01:56,616
Don't even get me started.

49
00:01:57,183 --> 00:01:58,685
Don't even go there.

50
00:01:58,751 --> 00:02:01,688
I had to do the laundry,
peel fruit, bring snacks…

51
00:02:01,754 --> 00:02:02,822
You had to peel fruit?

52
00:02:02,889 --> 00:02:04,224
-It's a long story.
-It is.

53
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:05,592
It was so back then.

54
00:02:05,658 --> 00:02:06,793
That's what Choi made him do.

55
00:02:08,862 --> 00:02:10,263
Be quiet. Don't let that go on air.

56
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:11,831
No? I'm sorry.

57
00:02:11,898 --> 00:02:13,066
Please bleep the name out.

58
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,300
WE DID

59
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:15,535
Well,

60
00:02:15,602 --> 00:02:19,439
I shared rooms with Bong Jung-keun,
Choo Shin-soo, and Song Eun-beom.

61
00:02:19,506 --> 00:02:22,709
<i>Among them, Eun-beom was an upperclassman</i>
<i>in middle and high school.</i>

62
00:02:22,775 --> 00:02:24,611
-That's intimidating.
-But…

63
00:02:24,677 --> 00:02:26,279
Shin-soo had given the job

64
00:02:26,346 --> 00:02:27,614
to Eun-beom.

65
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,482
SHIN-SOO (2ND ELDEST)
TO EUN-BEOM (3RD ELDEST)

66
00:02:29,549 --> 00:02:31,784
He wasn't the one who made me do it.

67
00:02:31,851 --> 00:02:33,353
So Eun-beom was the one?

68
00:02:33,419 --> 00:02:34,454
-Yes.
-That makes it ambiguous.

69
00:02:34,521 --> 00:02:36,689
It wasn't Shin-soo.

70
00:02:36,756 --> 00:02:39,259
But you didn't do the laundry.

71
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:41,461
-That was the gist of the story.
-Yes.

72
00:02:41,961 --> 00:02:45,231
Choo Shin-soo, our Choo Choo Train,

73
00:02:45,298 --> 00:02:49,669
is a legendary player
who set many firsts in the MLB.

74
00:02:49,736 --> 00:02:53,373
Recently, he was even nominated
for the MLB Hall of Fame.

75
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:55,175
-Yes.
-He's the first Korean.

76
00:02:55,241 --> 00:02:56,809
<i>He's the first Korean to be nominated.</i>

77
00:02:56,876 --> 00:02:59,412
<i>-The nomination itself is already…</i>
<i>-It's amazing.</i>

78
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,780
<i>When is the decision?</i>

79
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,348
It'll be announced in January.

80
00:03:02,415 --> 00:03:05,185
But I'm not getting my hopes up.

81
00:03:05,251 --> 00:03:06,619
Why not? You should.

82
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:10,657
-No, but if I make the Hall of Fame…
-If you do?

83
00:03:10,723 --> 00:03:13,459
Well, I'm sure my wife wouldn't want this,

84
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:16,629
but I can exchange everything I have
for that honor.

85
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:18,331
Is it that big?

86
00:03:18,398 --> 00:03:20,700
-Yes.
-It's the MLB Hall of Fame.

87
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:23,069
-Even financial belongings?
-My fortune, everything.

88
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:24,904
-You can even give those up.
-I can.

89
00:03:24,971 --> 00:03:28,541
Would you be willing to sacrifice anything
to make the Hall of Fame?

90
00:03:28,608 --> 00:03:30,877
-I'll just accept the award gladly.
-He'll just accept.

91
00:03:30,944 --> 00:03:33,379
-He'll just accept.
-That's how it usually goes.

92
00:03:33,446 --> 00:03:35,281
EYES SHUT

93
00:03:35,348 --> 00:03:37,617
-No need to give anything up.
-Just say, "Thank you."

94
00:03:37,684 --> 00:03:39,252
-What if he makes it?
-Never.

95
00:03:39,319 --> 00:03:41,221
What if? You never know.

96
00:03:41,287 --> 00:03:42,789
Then you'll have to give it up.

97
00:03:43,356 --> 00:03:44,891
I think I can do that.

98
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:46,893
-He's so cool!
-In that case,

99
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:47,927
can we release this?

100
00:03:47,994 --> 00:03:49,596
"WILL GIVE UP EVERYTHING
TO GET INTO THE HALL OF FAME"

101
00:03:49,662 --> 00:03:53,399
-That's how big of an honor it is.
-Yes, it's very significant.

102
00:03:53,466 --> 00:03:54,367
That's so cool.

103
00:03:54,434 --> 00:03:57,870
Someone among our chefs said
they admire Shin-soo and Hyun-jin

104
00:03:57,937 --> 00:03:59,105
in total awe.

105
00:03:59,172 --> 00:04:02,041
-That's not something people often say.
-In awe?

106
00:04:02,108 --> 00:04:03,409
-Who could it be?
-Who is it?

107
00:04:03,476 --> 00:04:05,245
It's probably me.

108
00:04:05,311 --> 00:04:07,513
-You?
-Chef Sung-jun

109
00:04:07,580 --> 00:04:09,949
-may be a huge baseball fan,
-Sure.

110
00:04:10,016 --> 00:04:12,585
-but I've actually played baseball.
-What?

111
00:04:12,652 --> 00:04:14,454
-Were you a player?
-Did you play?

112
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:17,390
No, but I've played amateur baseball.

113
00:04:17,457 --> 00:04:19,592
I woke up early in the morning
to go to Paldang area,

114
00:04:19,659 --> 00:04:21,060
made <i>eomuk-tang</i>, fish cake soup,

115
00:04:21,127 --> 00:04:24,063
-and played that early. I loved it.
-That's true.

116
00:04:24,130 --> 00:04:26,065
What's your position in your amateur team?

117
00:04:26,132 --> 00:04:27,900
-Pitcher.
-That's an important position.

118
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:29,369
Are you sure you didn't just make soup?

119
00:04:29,435 --> 00:04:31,304
I made <i>eomuk-tang</i> first.

120
00:04:31,371 --> 00:04:33,273
He suddenly sounds like the snack bar guy.

121
00:04:33,339 --> 00:04:35,074
It must've been famous for <i>eomuk-tang.</i>

122
00:04:35,141 --> 00:04:37,243
-I heard it was good.
-People thought you just went to cook…

123
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:39,178
-I almost wanted to go just to eat.
-…instead of playing baseball.

124
00:04:39,245 --> 00:04:40,980
-Shin-soo…
-I heard it was good.

125
00:04:41,047 --> 00:04:43,116
…do you happen to have
your baseball bat with you?

126
00:04:43,182 --> 00:04:45,051
May I borrow your bat?

127
00:04:45,585 --> 00:04:48,421
-I mean…
-He's serious about baseball. I know that.

128
00:04:48,488 --> 00:04:51,491
I found something like this.
He sent a video to our production crew.

129
00:04:51,557 --> 00:04:53,826
-He sent them a video?
-I wonder what it is.

130
00:04:53,893 --> 00:04:57,263
-He wanted them to show it to the guests.
-He must want to show himself off.

131
00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:59,265
Is it a video of you making <i>eomuk-tang?</i>

132
00:04:59,332 --> 00:05:00,800
I want to watch that!

133
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:02,201
I really want to try it too!

134
00:05:02,268 --> 00:05:05,171
-People must've huddled up on a cold day.
-Exactly!

135
00:05:05,238 --> 00:05:07,807
I want to watch him throw salt
into the soup like this.

136
00:05:07,874 --> 00:05:10,009
Let's watch the video he sent.

137
00:05:10,076 --> 00:05:10,977
-All right.
-How good is he?

138
00:05:13,046 --> 00:05:14,147
Huh?

139
00:05:14,213 --> 00:05:15,448
Is that you, Hyun-suk?

140
00:05:15,515 --> 00:05:17,050
-Really?
-<i>The pitcher?</i>

141
00:05:17,116 --> 00:05:18,651
<i>Are you wearing leggings?</i>

142
00:05:18,718 --> 00:05:20,286
LEGGINGS(?)

143
00:05:20,353 --> 00:05:21,454
<i>Those pants are tight.</i>

144
00:05:25,024 --> 00:05:26,626
NODS

145
00:05:26,693 --> 00:05:30,863
Well, it's kind of awkward to ask you
to evaluate an amateur player, but…

146
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:33,433
-He does have good pitching form.
-Does he?

147
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:35,935
-It's not bad, but there's one thing.
-Okay.

148
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,637
Pitchers are supposed to throw

149
00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:39,272
-to the catcher.
-Yes.

150
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:41,774
But when he winds up,

151
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:43,776
he's looking somewhere else.

152
00:05:43,843 --> 00:05:45,912
<i>-You should look at the catcher.</i>
<i>-He wanted to look cool.</i>

153
00:05:45,978 --> 00:05:48,181
-He wants to look cool.
-He needs to look good.

154
00:05:48,247 --> 00:05:49,349
"Do I look cool right now?"

155
00:05:49,415 --> 00:05:53,119
-"Am I throwing like a cool pitcher?" Yes.
-You should look where you're throwing.

156
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:54,253
-That's right.
-The catcher.

157
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:55,822
-Look at the catcher.
-But you looked this way,

158
00:05:55,888 --> 00:05:57,123
-lifted, and pitched.
-He did that.

159
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:59,592
-Just as Hyun-jin did just now.
-That's right.

160
00:05:59,659 --> 00:06:02,829
You looked that way, lifted, and pitched.

161
00:06:03,396 --> 00:06:05,565
SUCH AN ACCURATE ANALYSIS

162
00:06:05,631 --> 00:06:07,300
-It's all about coolness.
-He looked elsewhere.

163
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,802
-He was only conscious about the angle.
-You're right.

164
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:11,504
He only wanted to show his jawline.

165
00:06:11,571 --> 00:06:13,840
-But the posture was excellent.
-Who cares where the ball goes?

166
00:06:13,906 --> 00:06:15,675
-It didn't matter.
-You're right.

167
00:06:15,742 --> 00:06:17,076
What do you think as a batter?

168
00:06:17,143 --> 00:06:19,479
A pitcher who has no control
makes me nervous.

169
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:22,048
TRIGGERED

170
00:06:22,115 --> 00:06:23,883
You made the batter anxious!

171
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:25,051
-It's scary.
-You might get hit.

172
00:06:25,118 --> 00:06:27,720
My control wasn't so bad for an amateur.

173
00:06:27,787 --> 00:06:30,189
I pitch curveballs, sliders,
and forkballs,

174
00:06:30,256 --> 00:06:33,793
and on a good day,
the score looks amazing.

175
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:35,695
Do you even know how to pitch?

176
00:06:35,762 --> 00:06:38,264
-But you're an amateur.
-He's dead serious.

177
00:06:38,331 --> 00:06:40,867
That was his most serious moment yet.

178
00:06:40,933 --> 00:06:42,635
He did play hard, though. I know that.

179
00:06:42,702 --> 00:06:44,036
-When?
-When was that?

180
00:06:44,103 --> 00:06:45,605
-A decade ago.
-A decade ago?

181
00:06:45,671 --> 00:06:46,939
I'd break my arm if I did that now.

182
00:06:47,006 --> 00:06:49,041
-Your salt throwing pose was odd lately.
-I knew it.

183
00:06:49,108 --> 00:06:51,077
That's why he keeps missing the food.

184
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:53,746
-Be quiet.
-He doesn't look!

185
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:56,749
-<i>He should've looked first.</i>
-His control has been the worst lately!

186
00:06:56,816 --> 00:06:58,117
You need to look before you throw.

187
00:06:58,184 --> 00:06:59,919
-In here.
-I have good control,

188
00:06:59,986 --> 00:07:02,488
but the doctor said
I had torn my rotator cuff.

189
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:05,825
I used to be an overhand salt thrower,

190
00:07:05,892 --> 00:07:08,528
but it kept dropping
from a three-quarter arm angle.

191
00:07:08,594 --> 00:07:11,631
-And now…
-Are we talking about pitching or salt?

192
00:07:11,697 --> 00:07:14,534
-Salt.
-People might think you're a ballplayer.

193
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,436
You tried so hard and tore your tendon.

194
00:07:16,502 --> 00:07:19,005
-All right.
-We're here with two Major League players,

195
00:07:19,071 --> 00:07:21,207
listening to the story
of an amateur player.

196
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:22,175
I'm sorry.

197
00:07:22,241 --> 00:07:23,476
Please edit out my entire story.

198
00:07:23,543 --> 00:07:24,977
HMPH, I'M SULKING

199
00:07:25,044 --> 00:07:26,612
I plead with you.

200
00:07:26,679 --> 00:07:28,881
All Korean amateur players
must stop playing!

201
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:30,883
You need to stop! Come on!

202
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:33,920
Someone put him to sleep.
Shoot him with your poison dart!

203
00:07:33,986 --> 00:07:35,221
Please go to sleep.

204
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:37,990
-Among our chefs,
-Yes, change the subject. Cut him out.

205
00:07:38,057 --> 00:07:40,626
someone has watched
Shin-soo's game in person.

206
00:07:41,194 --> 00:07:42,128
WOW

207
00:07:42,195 --> 00:07:44,030
-Who is it?
-You must've seen it in America.

208
00:07:44,096 --> 00:07:44,997
IT'S ME

209
00:07:45,064 --> 00:07:46,365
Chef Jong-won? In America?

210
00:07:46,432 --> 00:07:48,301
Yes, when he played in Cleveland,

211
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:51,737
my school was in the next state,
so I went and watched him play.

212
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:56,209
Back then, cultural phenomena
like K-pop weren't as prevalent yet,

213
00:07:56,275 --> 00:07:59,779
so it was very encouraging
for international students

214
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:02,281
that there was a Korean player in the MLB.

215
00:08:02,348 --> 00:08:03,883
It makes you proud.

216
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:06,486
Mr. Amateur Player,
have you ever watched him play in the MLB?

217
00:08:06,552 --> 00:08:08,821
-No.
-No?

218
00:08:08,888 --> 00:08:10,289
-Listen.
-Then just keep it down.

219
00:08:10,356 --> 00:08:11,591
He's just a fan,

220
00:08:11,657 --> 00:08:13,426
and he just watched a game abroad.

221
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:15,394
Yet you were impressed by their stories.

222
00:08:15,461 --> 00:08:17,463
So why must an amateur player like me

223
00:08:17,530 --> 00:08:19,265
who not only loved,
but also played baseball

224
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,300
be harassed like this?

225
00:08:21,868 --> 00:08:23,636
MR. AMATEUR PLAYER FEELS WRONGED

226
00:08:23,703 --> 00:08:24,837
Poison him again.

227
00:08:24,904 --> 00:08:26,105
This isn't working.

228
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,673
-Shoot your poison darts.
-It doesn't work.

229
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,442
There's a tip from the production crew.

230
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:32,245
-This sounds quite controversial.
-What is it?

231
00:08:32,311 --> 00:08:33,946
"I'm the Choo Shin-soo among chefs."

232
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:35,615
-Who said that?
-Who is it?

233
00:08:36,582 --> 00:08:38,017
-Was it you?
-Who is it?

234
00:08:38,084 --> 00:08:39,919
-I didn't expect this.
-Choo Choo Train?

235
00:08:39,986 --> 00:08:41,420
-Sam Kim.
-It was Sam.

236
00:08:41,487 --> 00:08:42,922
Did you say this, Sam?

237
00:08:42,989 --> 00:08:44,490
-How so?
-"I'm the Choo Shin-soo among chefs."

238
00:08:44,557 --> 00:08:45,958
-Sam Sam Train.
-Wait.

239
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:48,127
Sam Sam Train? Just like Choo Choo Train.

240
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:50,997
-Hey!
-What did you mean by this?

241
00:08:51,063 --> 00:08:54,700
I was an Asian who worked in America.

242
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:57,236
And a way for an Asian man
to stand out at workplaces

243
00:08:57,303 --> 00:08:59,272
was to be at work two to three hours early

244
00:08:59,338 --> 00:09:00,706
<i>to get everything ready</i>

245
00:09:00,773 --> 00:09:03,876
<i>and work extra shifts even on my days off.</i>

246
00:09:03,943 --> 00:09:06,913
I heard he was always early
and practiced very hard,

247
00:09:06,979 --> 00:09:09,348
-so I meant it in that aspect.
-He's diligent.

248
00:09:09,415 --> 00:09:10,349
I'm sorry to say this,

249
00:09:10,416 --> 00:09:13,019
but Sam is always the last to arrive
whenever we shoot this show.

250
00:09:13,085 --> 00:09:14,420
SLOW SAM SAM TRAIN

251
00:09:14,487 --> 00:09:15,955
-And he won't talk.
-He doesn't talk.

252
00:09:16,022 --> 00:09:17,390
-My gosh.
-You two aren't so alike.

253
00:09:17,456 --> 00:09:20,226
-Sam Sam Train.
-I want to be like him.

254
00:09:20,293 --> 00:09:21,227
You're in the "Major League" now.

255
00:09:21,294 --> 00:09:24,130
Things must've been very hard for you
when you were in the Minor League.

256
00:09:24,196 --> 00:09:25,998
-Yes.
-Was your diet the toughest?

257
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:28,568
Food was such a rough part of the journey.

258
00:09:28,634 --> 00:09:31,404
We only got two loaves of bread
right before the game.

259
00:09:31,470 --> 00:09:33,239
-Really? Why?
-That's rough.

260
00:09:33,306 --> 00:09:36,742
At first, we only got
strawberry jam and peanut butter.

261
00:09:36,809 --> 00:09:38,911
-That's awful.
-And if you're late, you don't get any.

262
00:09:39,512 --> 00:09:41,280
I heard
you don't eat peanut butter anymore

263
00:09:41,347 --> 00:09:43,049
because you had too much back then.

264
00:09:43,115 --> 00:09:45,418
I had such a rough time back then,

265
00:09:45,484 --> 00:09:47,320
-so I don't really eat it now.
-I get it.

266
00:09:47,386 --> 00:09:49,555
-So don't use peanuts.
-That'd be the case.

267
00:09:49,622 --> 00:09:54,293
Did you feel quite bad for your wife
when you played in the Minor League?

268
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:56,929
My wife loves seafood,

269
00:09:56,996 --> 00:09:59,799
so it broke my heart
that I couldn't get it for her.

270
00:09:59,865 --> 00:10:03,235
<i>When I first played for the Seattle team</i>
<i>in the Major League,</i>

271
00:10:03,302 --> 00:10:06,772
seafood was extremely fresh in Seattle,

272
00:10:06,839 --> 00:10:09,942
so they served all kinds of seafood,
such as snow crabs and shrimp.

273
00:10:10,009 --> 00:10:12,178
They also had tubs of sushi.

274
00:10:12,244 --> 00:10:13,079
SEAFOOD PARADISE

275
00:10:13,145 --> 00:10:16,816
So when I came down to the Minor League
after living that life,

276
00:10:16,882 --> 00:10:18,351
I couldn't sleep anymore.

277
00:10:18,417 --> 00:10:19,819
-When I looked up,
-It's even sadder.

278
00:10:19,885 --> 00:10:23,723
I could vividly imagine all the food.

279
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:25,591
-You imagined that?
-I'm serious.

280
00:10:25,658 --> 00:10:28,461
It wasn't the ballpark or anything,
but the food.

281
00:10:28,527 --> 00:10:30,162
-The food.
-And the facility too.

282
00:10:30,229 --> 00:10:34,500
What was the food like for you
at the Major League, Hyun-jin?

283
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:36,902
I just started…

284
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,738
LAUGHS

285
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:40,740
STRAIGHT TO THE MLB

286
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:44,110
-I enjoyed the food for 11 years.
-Deliciously.

287
00:10:44,844 --> 00:10:47,980
You two must've become tighter,
and your love must've grown deeper

288
00:10:48,047 --> 00:10:49,415
<i>as you lived through tough years.</i>

289
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:52,218
We received another tip
from the production crew.

290
00:10:52,284 --> 00:10:55,488
It's that Hyun-jin and his wife
visited Shin-soo's place in America

291
00:10:55,554 --> 00:10:59,225
and robbed everything they had
in their fridge.

292
00:10:59,291 --> 00:11:01,627
-What did you take?
-You need to explain this.

293
00:11:01,694 --> 00:11:03,129
When you go to his place,

294
00:11:03,195 --> 00:11:06,532
he has the best of everything, even water.
He even drinks the best water.

295
00:11:06,599 --> 00:11:09,435
-The best water? Bedrock water?
-What's the best water?

296
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:11,704
-Is he talking about Evian?
-What is it?

297
00:11:11,771 --> 00:11:15,374
He has the best water,
which helps him stay hydrated.

298
00:11:15,441 --> 00:11:18,944
And he has lots of healthy food
in his pantry.

299
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:21,647
So when Shin-soo got a little tipsy,

300
00:11:21,714 --> 00:11:25,451
I always stole his food,
saying, "Hey, I'm taking this!"

301
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:26,852
So my wife and I…

302
00:11:26,919 --> 00:11:28,587
THE STEALING MONSTER

303
00:11:29,188 --> 00:11:30,289
MUST LOAD UP ON SHIN-SOO'S STUFF

304
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:31,891
-When he was a little tipsy?
-Yes.

305
00:11:32,458 --> 00:11:36,262
So I made use of Shin-soo's pantry
quite often.

306
00:11:36,328 --> 00:11:38,698
-You didn't know?
-I did.

307
00:11:38,764 --> 00:11:39,832
You were tipsy, but you knew.

308
00:11:39,899 --> 00:11:41,767
But I was tipsy and all, so…

309
00:11:41,834 --> 00:11:43,235
AS YOU WISH

310
00:11:43,302 --> 00:11:44,503
-You flexed.
-"Take it."

311
00:11:44,570 --> 00:11:47,306
Come the next day,
I'd look at the empty space

312
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:48,474
and feel heartbroken.

313
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:51,343
If you could see empty space,
he must've taken a lot.

314
00:11:51,410 --> 00:11:53,312
So where did you bring those fridges from?

315
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:55,448
-My place in Korea.
-In Korea.

316
00:11:55,514 --> 00:11:57,516
I wonder how much food he has inside.

317
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:59,785
I wonder what he keeps inside.

318
00:11:59,852 --> 00:12:03,622
We're about to go through
Shin-soo's fridge.

319
00:12:03,689 --> 00:12:05,057
I heard your wife

320
00:12:05,124 --> 00:12:07,359
gave you special training
after hearing you'd be here.

321
00:12:07,426 --> 00:12:09,195
Yes, she showed me every single one

322
00:12:09,261 --> 00:12:12,031
and explained what we had inside.

323
00:12:12,098 --> 00:12:13,466
INGREDIENT LECTURE FROM WIFE

324
00:12:13,532 --> 00:12:15,801
-She didn't want me to make a mistake.
-To not make mistakes.

325
00:12:15,868 --> 00:12:18,237
Thank you so much.

326
00:12:18,304 --> 00:12:20,406
He came here after his wife's training.

327
00:12:20,473 --> 00:12:23,476
And now, we present Shin-soo's fridge!

328
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:26,579
IT'S A PARTY

329
00:12:26,645 --> 00:12:28,914
We present Shin-soo's fridge!

330
00:12:28,981 --> 00:12:31,584
-This one looks great too.
-My goodness.

331
00:12:31,650 --> 00:12:32,918
It's fully loaded.

332
00:12:32,985 --> 00:12:34,720
-What's that?
-What are the black things?

333
00:12:34,787 --> 00:12:38,257
-Are those beverages in the middle?
-Everything is so neatly organized.

334
00:12:38,324 --> 00:12:41,894
Yes, I hate seeing disorganized things.

335
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:44,630
I need to know where things are
even with my eyes closed.

336
00:12:44,697 --> 00:12:45,931
THAT'S HIS PERSONALITY

337
00:12:45,998 --> 00:12:47,399
He has everything lined up neatly.

338
00:12:47,466 --> 00:12:49,034
We'll begin from the first shelf.

339
00:12:49,101 --> 00:12:52,004
Hyun-jin's fridge
also had pork belly at the very top.

340
00:12:52,071 --> 00:12:53,939
Look how huge this is.

341
00:12:54,006 --> 00:12:56,208
-Whole pork belly.
-Yes.

342
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,943
What's next to this? My goodness.

343
00:12:58,010 --> 00:13:01,380
I see why Hyun-jin
wanted to steal from him.

344
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:03,983
He has salmon… These are salmon too.

345
00:13:04,049 --> 00:13:05,651
-Those are smoked salmon.
-Smoked salmon.

346
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:06,552
And raw salmon.

347
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:09,655
I don't really like salmon,

348
00:13:09,722 --> 00:13:12,958
but if I had to eat it,
it has to be grilled or smoked.

349
00:13:14,193 --> 00:13:15,127
I see.

350
00:13:15,194 --> 00:13:18,130
-These are mussels.
-Mussels.

351
00:13:18,197 --> 00:13:19,165
MUSSEL, SURF CLAM, OYSTER

352
00:13:19,231 --> 00:13:20,633
You have lots of seafood.

353
00:13:20,699 --> 00:13:22,168
He has all kinds of delicacies.

354
00:13:22,234 --> 00:13:24,170
What's your favorite seafood?

355
00:13:24,236 --> 00:13:26,572
-Mussels are my favorite.
-Mussels.

356
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:28,741
-He likes these. Mussels.
-Mussels are good.

357
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:30,409
Do you enjoy seafood?

358
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:33,679
I'm mostly into meat,
but my wife loves seafood.

359
00:13:33,746 --> 00:13:36,015
So when we go out to eat,

360
00:13:36,081 --> 00:13:38,617
I try to find a seafood restaurant
rather than a red meat restaurant.

361
00:13:38,684 --> 00:13:41,787
Because she feels too uncomfortable
and won't go if I don't eat it.

362
00:13:41,854 --> 00:13:44,890
So I changed my palate
to make sure she had something.

363
00:13:44,957 --> 00:13:48,327
-He's a romanticist.
-He is.

364
00:13:48,394 --> 00:13:50,462
I see something covered in foil.

365
00:13:50,529 --> 00:13:52,164
Are these potatoes? What are these?

366
00:13:52,231 --> 00:13:53,666
Those are avocados.

367
00:13:53,732 --> 00:13:55,401
-Avocados?
-Avocados.

368
00:13:56,101 --> 00:13:58,704
This was something I learned from my wife.

369
00:13:58,771 --> 00:14:01,640
She taught you something?
Tell us what it is.

370
00:14:01,707 --> 00:14:03,676
Is it mushy?

371
00:14:03,742 --> 00:14:06,378
-Just a little. I think it's ripe.
-I see.

372
00:14:06,445 --> 00:14:10,616
It's perfect to eat
when it pushes in just a bit.

373
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:13,452
She kept them wrapped in foil
to make sure they lasted longer.

374
00:14:14,453 --> 00:14:16,355
He's been trained well.

375
00:14:16,422 --> 00:14:18,324
Yes, as soon as he saw those,
he said, "Avocados."

376
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,692
HE IMMEDIATELY SAID AVOCADOS

377
00:14:19,758 --> 00:14:21,227
He said, "Avocados."

378
00:14:22,228 --> 00:14:23,762
Most wouldn't know what they are.

379
00:14:23,829 --> 00:14:25,898
They'd be confused,
but he said, "Avocados."

380
00:14:25,965 --> 00:14:26,932
His question was funny too.

381
00:14:26,999 --> 00:14:28,367
-"Is it mushy?"
-Is it mushy?

382
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:31,003
She must've told him to ask the hosts.

383
00:14:31,070 --> 00:14:32,805
Look at the third shelf.

384
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,073
Is this water too?

385
00:14:34,139 --> 00:14:35,207
-That's coffee.
-Coffee.

386
00:14:35,274 --> 00:14:36,976
Coffee? It's coffee?

387
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:39,078
I didn't use to drink coffee

388
00:14:39,144 --> 00:14:40,779
because I heard caffeine was bad for you.

389
00:14:40,846 --> 00:14:44,617
But when I first met my wife,
she was always drinking coffee.

390
00:14:44,683 --> 00:14:45,985
I adjusted to her palate.

391
00:14:46,051 --> 00:14:49,822
I began to drink coffee,
now I became addicted.

392
00:14:50,589 --> 00:14:54,693
-The lover boy in the world of baseball.
-What? The lover boy?

393
00:14:55,261 --> 00:14:56,328
THAT'S SO APPROPRIATE

394
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:58,898
I see some tofu. Do you like tofu?

395
00:14:58,964 --> 00:15:01,267
I don't prefer store-bought tofu, though.

396
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:05,070
But at times, my wife makes some at home.

397
00:15:05,137 --> 00:15:07,773
-That's a huge task. It's not easy.
-She makes tofu?

398
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,276
She blends the soybeans, steams them,

399
00:15:10,342 --> 00:15:12,544
and does everything,
adding coagulant and all.

400
00:15:12,611 --> 00:15:15,714
She said she'd make some
before I came here,

401
00:15:15,781 --> 00:15:19,485
but I wanted to keep them to myself
instead of bringing them here.

402
00:15:19,551 --> 00:15:21,086
OH MY GOODNESS

403
00:15:21,153 --> 00:15:23,055
Did you stop her from doing too much work?

404
00:15:23,122 --> 00:15:25,591
It would've been great
if you let us see it.

405
00:15:25,658 --> 00:15:27,660
Of course, I should be
the only one who eats it,

406
00:15:27,726 --> 00:15:29,528
but I also want to be
the only one to see it.

407
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:30,996
THE CHOO CHOO TRAIN OF LOVE

408
00:15:31,063 --> 00:15:32,231
HAHAHAHA

409
00:15:32,298 --> 00:15:35,467
-And that's it for…
-You're worse than Jung-hwan!

410
00:15:35,534 --> 00:15:37,836
-I'm sorry.
-My gosh.

411
00:15:37,903 --> 00:15:40,306
I see the veggies in here. Carrots,

412
00:15:40,372 --> 00:15:43,175
eggplants, and cabbage.

413
00:15:43,242 --> 00:15:46,812
I never eat carrots or eggplants.

414
00:15:46,879 --> 00:15:48,113
But they're here.

415
00:15:48,180 --> 00:15:50,316
The only way I'll eat eggplants
is when my wife makes

416
00:15:50,382 --> 00:15:52,851
-eggplant rice in a hot stone pot.
-Eggplant hot stone pot rice.

417
00:15:52,918 --> 00:15:55,754
Then it doesn't taste like eggplants.
It tastes more like meat.

418
00:15:55,821 --> 00:15:57,623
-The texture.
-Yes.

419
00:15:57,690 --> 00:16:02,328
-And carrots have a particular smell.
-The smell?

420
00:16:02,394 --> 00:16:04,129
-So when I eat curry,
-It's loud.

421
00:16:04,196 --> 00:16:06,065
I pick it all out.

422
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:07,566
CHOO CHOO TRAIN WAS A PICKY EATER

423
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,468
Do you pick those out
like kids who are picky?

424
00:16:09,535 --> 00:16:11,603
She began to julienne them
to stop me from doing that.

425
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:13,739
To stop you from picking those out?

426
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:16,408
She does that
like she would teach a child.

427
00:16:16,475 --> 00:16:18,243
Look! As we speak,

428
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:20,479
I just spotted peanut butter!

429
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:22,514
He said he got sick of it

430
00:16:22,581 --> 00:16:24,450
-and stopped eating it.
-He did.

431
00:16:24,516 --> 00:16:27,853
My wife probably got it for herself.
I don't think it's for me.

432
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,388
He doesn't eat it.

433
00:16:29,455 --> 00:16:31,991
Well, it is delicious.

434
00:16:32,057 --> 00:16:34,026
And down here is the freezer.

435
00:16:34,093 --> 00:16:35,461
Scallops.

436
00:16:35,527 --> 00:16:36,395
-Cutlassfish.
-Cutlassfish.

437
00:16:36,462 --> 00:16:40,399
-He has lots of fish.
-A lot. And squid.

438
00:16:40,466 --> 00:16:41,467
What's this?

439
00:16:41,533 --> 00:16:43,869
That's soybean pulp,
left after my wife made tofu.

440
00:16:43,936 --> 00:16:45,571
-Soybean pulp.
-It's soybean pulp.

441
00:16:45,637 --> 00:16:48,107
I didn't want to bring her tofu,
so you can look at the pulp.

442
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:50,442
YOU'RE IMPOSSIBLE

443
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:52,211
You're really something, lover boy.

444
00:16:52,277 --> 00:16:53,112
HAHAHAHA

445
00:16:53,946 --> 00:16:55,114
Goodness gracious.

446
00:16:55,881 --> 00:16:58,917
-The next one. He has another fridge.
-There's two.

447
00:16:58,984 --> 00:17:00,586
He has another one. Let's take a look.

448
00:17:00,652 --> 00:17:03,455
We present the next fridge.

449
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:05,224
-Kimchi.
-Kimchi and side dishes.

450
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:07,426
-Not here.
-Most of these are kimchi,

451
00:17:07,493 --> 00:17:08,961
-and these over here, alcohol.
-Yes.

452
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:11,530
Wait, she must've made this.

453
00:17:11,597 --> 00:17:13,999
-Yes, she made it recently.
-Just recently?

454
00:17:14,066 --> 00:17:15,034
Is it freshly…

455
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:16,301
TA-DA

456
00:17:16,368 --> 00:17:18,637
Do you help her when she makes kimchi?

457
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:20,739
Yes, I'm in charge
of all the heavy lifting.

458
00:17:20,806 --> 00:17:22,708
-Heavy lifting? Such as?
-Of course.

459
00:17:22,775 --> 00:17:24,843
I salt the napa cabbages,

460
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:26,945
-wash them, wring them,
-Wring and cut.

461
00:17:27,012 --> 00:17:28,347
and move them everywhere.

462
00:17:28,414 --> 00:17:30,149
-That's hard work.
-Yes, you have to move them.

463
00:17:30,215 --> 00:17:32,785
We have a photo of Shin-soo making kimchi.

464
00:17:32,851 --> 00:17:33,752
SHIN-SOO MAKES KIMCHI?

465
00:17:33,819 --> 00:17:34,953
Show us the picture.

466
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:36,755
You really did it!

467
00:17:36,822 --> 00:17:40,192
-He made all of that?
-You actually made kimchi.

468
00:17:40,259 --> 00:17:43,695
Is the kimchi you make with your wife
always delicious?

469
00:17:43,762 --> 00:17:45,064
Everything she makes is good.

470
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:46,932
-All right. Sure.
-"Sure."

471
00:17:46,999 --> 00:17:50,335
All right. I shouldn't have asked.

472
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:52,471
What's this?
Green onion kimchi is all lined up.

473
00:17:52,538 --> 00:17:53,372
GREEN ONION KIMCHI

474
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:55,207
LINED UP

475
00:17:55,274 --> 00:17:57,543
-You must be so organized.
-Lined up.

476
00:17:57,609 --> 00:18:00,646
And the drinks are lined up too.

477
00:18:00,712 --> 00:18:03,749
I feel like the time I spend
with my wife over a drink

478
00:18:03,816 --> 00:18:05,818
is how I wrap up the day.

479
00:18:05,884 --> 00:18:08,620
Because I'm often away from home,

480
00:18:08,687 --> 00:18:11,423
<i>I hear everything about</i>
<i>how my three kids are doing at school</i>

481
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:13,459
<i>and what they're going through</i>

482
00:18:13,525 --> 00:18:16,995
while I have a drink with my wife.

483
00:18:17,729 --> 00:18:20,032
She'd suggest the things
I should tell them as a father

484
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:22,468
and everything else during that time.

485
00:18:22,534 --> 00:18:25,671
You two must be
having a great time these days.

486
00:18:25,737 --> 00:18:29,675
Our kids are all grown up
and at boarding schools in America.

487
00:18:29,741 --> 00:18:31,477
So it feels like a second honeymoon.

488
00:18:31,543 --> 00:18:35,047
-I never got to enjoy the first one.
-I see.

489
00:18:36,048 --> 00:18:38,784
And that was the loving fridge
of a lover boy

490
00:18:38,851 --> 00:18:42,387
who has been enjoying
his second honeymoon.

491
00:18:43,989 --> 00:18:47,159
-My gosh.
-Wasn't he a ballplayer, not a lover?

492
00:18:48,327 --> 00:18:50,262
We will now decide on the matchups.

493
00:18:50,329 --> 00:18:52,097
The matches for this episode

494
00:18:52,164 --> 00:18:54,867
are the final matches

495
00:18:54,933 --> 00:18:58,070
for the 2025 regular season
of <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

496
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:01,607
Next week, we will hold the championship.

497
00:19:01,673 --> 00:19:05,344
<i>The championship will be played</i>
<i>just like the baseball playoffs.</i>

498
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:08,647
<i>It starts with fourth versus fifth,</i>
<i>and then the winner moves up.</i>

499
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:11,884
<i>In the end, we'll find out</i>
<i>who the best chef was this year.</i>

500
00:19:11,950 --> 00:19:15,888
We've put in the results
from the previous episode.

501
00:19:15,954 --> 00:19:17,022
Show us the current ranking.

502
00:19:17,089 --> 00:19:18,590
CURRENT RANKING (2025 SEASON)

503
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:20,626
Today is the final regular season.

504
00:19:20,692 --> 00:19:25,364
Chef Hyun-suk is confirmed as first place,
regardless of how he does today.

505
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:28,433
If two have the same number of wins,
the one with fewer losses will lead.

506
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:30,802
After the match
with Hyun-jin's ingredients,

507
00:19:30,869 --> 00:19:34,006
Chef Eun-yeong made her way
up to third place.

508
00:19:34,072 --> 00:19:35,440
She has nine wins and six losses.

509
00:19:35,507 --> 00:19:37,009
Ho-young, nine wins, seven losses.

510
00:19:37,075 --> 00:19:39,378
Jong-won, nine wins, nine losses.

511
00:19:39,444 --> 00:19:43,515
If Ho-young and Jong-won
lose today's match,

512
00:19:43,582 --> 00:19:47,085
<i>Chef Eun-yeong has fewer losses,</i>

513
00:19:47,152 --> 00:19:49,922
<i>-so you cannot surpass her.</i>
<i>-</i>We can be in fifth place.

514
00:19:49,988 --> 00:19:54,159
<i>But if you win today,</i>
<i>you can move past Poong.</i>

515
00:19:54,226 --> 00:19:57,095
<i>-You can take second place.</i>
<i>-Up to second place.</i>

516
00:19:57,162 --> 00:20:00,132
There's a chance
that all four places change,

517
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:01,166
everyone but Hyun-suk.

518
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:03,802
-It changes a lot.
-Yes, it'll change drastically.

519
00:20:03,869 --> 00:20:06,672
-I want to fight Sam.
-I think they should have a cook-off.

520
00:20:06,738 --> 00:20:09,875
If they partake in different rounds
and both win,

521
00:20:09,942 --> 00:20:11,543
I would hate that.

522
00:20:12,511 --> 00:20:14,112
-You're right.
-You two should fight!

523
00:20:14,179 --> 00:20:16,648
-That'd drop your ranking.
-You can go down to fourth.

524
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:17,683
You can.

525
00:20:17,749 --> 00:20:18,817
You two should fight.

526
00:20:18,884 --> 00:20:21,486
There isn't a lot of difference
between the fourth and the fifth.

527
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:23,822
So here are the remaining chefs.

528
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:26,358
Choi Hyun-suk, Jung Ho-young,
and Son Jong-won.

529
00:20:26,425 --> 00:20:29,094
Sam is just here for the show today.

530
00:20:29,161 --> 00:20:32,898
However, Sam can… It's like this
at the end of the baseball season.

531
00:20:32,965 --> 00:20:35,334
-Sabotage.
-Yes, you can sabotage players.

532
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,835
A-HA

533
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:38,570
-He can do that.
-Yes, you're out anyway.

534
00:20:38,637 --> 00:20:39,571
All right, now.

535
00:20:39,638 --> 00:20:42,441
Let's find out what Shin-soo wants to eat.

536
00:20:42,507 --> 00:20:44,409
These are his orders.

537
00:20:44,476 --> 00:20:45,344
Show us!

538
00:20:45,877 --> 00:20:48,880
-First, Want Choo Overcome Picky Eating.
-Want Choo Overcome Picky Eating.

539
00:20:48,947 --> 00:20:50,215
Want Choo.

540
00:20:50,282 --> 00:20:52,284
-You mentioned the things you didn't eat.
-Yes.

541
00:20:52,351 --> 00:20:55,220
-Carrots and eggplants.
-Yes, carrots and eggplants.

542
00:20:55,287 --> 00:20:56,622
Are you okay with peanut butter?

543
00:20:56,688 --> 00:20:59,224
DEEP CONTEMPLATION

544
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:02,060
I'll reminisce the old days and try it.

545
00:21:02,127 --> 00:21:04,196
Carrots, eggplants, and peanut butter.

546
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:07,599
I want to know if there's a way
for me to enjoy them,

547
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:10,269
so that I can actually eat the dishes
that contain them.

548
00:21:10,335 --> 00:21:12,671
I think that could
make things easier for my wife.

549
00:21:12,738 --> 00:21:15,540
-Okay.
-And the next order. The second one.

550
00:21:16,341 --> 00:21:19,077
-Seafood Bar Snack, Want Choo.
-Want you.

551
00:21:19,144 --> 00:21:20,312
-Seafood Bar Snack, Want Choo.
-Bar snack?

552
00:21:20,379 --> 00:21:23,548
My wife loves seafood,

553
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:26,818
so I want something we can have
as a bar snack with our drink.

554
00:21:26,885 --> 00:21:28,754
-Your second honeymoon.
-Yes.

555
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:32,457
I want to eat something delicious
made with seafood.

556
00:21:32,524 --> 00:21:34,092
Because his wife loves seafood.

557
00:21:34,693 --> 00:21:37,896
We're here today
with the lover boy of baseball.

558
00:21:39,431 --> 00:21:41,733
Now, we'll decide on the matchups.

559
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,770
Hyun-suk, Ho-young,
Jong-won, and Sam remain.

560
00:21:44,836 --> 00:21:47,939
We'll give first place a chance to choose.

561
00:21:48,006 --> 00:21:49,875
I also am a picky eater,

562
00:21:49,941 --> 00:21:52,177
a picky eater who only devours stars.

563
00:21:52,911 --> 00:21:53,945
No way.

564
00:21:54,012 --> 00:21:56,181
I'll go
with Want Choo Overcome Picky Eating.

565
00:21:56,248 --> 00:21:58,083
Picky Eating for Hyun-suk.

566
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:00,419
He wants to help him
overcome picky eating.

567
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:03,955
Ho-young and Jong-won
are looking right and left.

568
00:22:04,022 --> 00:22:05,157
In that case,

569
00:22:05,223 --> 00:22:07,092
we'll give Sam the next choice.

570
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:09,094
-These are the last matches of the season.
-Yes.

571
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:10,629
So I wish to fight
with the 1st place winner.

572
00:22:10,696 --> 00:22:12,898
I'LL FIGHT 1ST PLACE!

573
00:22:12,964 --> 00:22:13,965
That's it!

574
00:22:14,032 --> 00:22:16,234
THANKS TO SAM, POONG SECURES 3RD PLACE

575
00:22:16,301 --> 00:22:18,503
You'll think of this
as the final championship round.

576
00:22:18,570 --> 00:22:20,539
-My own final round.
-Your own.

577
00:22:20,605 --> 00:22:21,840
A championship for himself.

578
00:22:21,907 --> 00:22:26,178
That means Ho-young and Jong-won
will make seafood bar snacks.

579
00:22:26,244 --> 00:22:28,213
After this round,
one of you will be second place,

580
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:31,016
-and the other, in fifth place.
-Second or fifth.

581
00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:32,818
-That's a bloody round.
-All right, then.

582
00:22:32,884 --> 00:22:35,053
Let us begin the first round.

583
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:38,156
The current first place, Hyun-suk,
versus Sam, who's already out of the game.

584
00:22:38,223 --> 00:22:41,660
THE CHAMPIONSHIP FINAL BEGINS

585
00:22:41,727 --> 00:22:46,098
<i>We're about to begin the first round</i>
<i>with ingredients from Shin-soo's fridge.</i>

586
00:22:46,164 --> 00:22:49,167
Here to alleviate
Shin-soo's habit of picky eating,

587
00:22:49,234 --> 00:22:52,104
the two picky eaters of the show
stand in the kitchen.

588
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:56,375
Chef Choi Hyun-suk,
who gets picky and only devours stars.

589
00:22:56,441 --> 00:22:58,944
On the other hand,

590
00:22:59,010 --> 00:23:03,648
the picky-eater chef that only picks out
the stars, Chef Sam Kim, is here.

591
00:23:03,715 --> 00:23:06,885
We have another deposition
of Sam's testimony.

592
00:23:06,952 --> 00:23:08,253
-Really?
-Yes.

593
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:10,756
"The chef who'll fight him

594
00:23:10,822 --> 00:23:12,491
in the final round
of the actual championship

595
00:23:12,557 --> 00:23:15,560
should start thanking me right now."

596
00:23:15,627 --> 00:23:16,461
-Why?
-Why?

597
00:23:16,528 --> 00:23:18,330
Will you break his arm during the round?

598
00:23:18,397 --> 00:23:20,031
LIKE THIS?

599
00:23:20,098 --> 00:23:21,833
-He's been doing well, right?
-Yes.

600
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,235
So if I win this round,

601
00:23:23,301 --> 00:23:25,036
the next chef will feel more confident.

602
00:23:25,103 --> 00:23:27,239
-That's a possibility.
-It'll be easier.

603
00:23:27,939 --> 00:23:30,542
-He wants to break his rise.
-He wants to break it.

604
00:23:30,609 --> 00:23:34,079
Actually, it's impossible
for Sam to break my spirit.

605
00:23:34,146 --> 00:23:35,414
I'm currently in first place,

606
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:36,715
but this guy is

607
00:23:36,782 --> 00:23:38,183
outside of the ranking.

608
00:23:39,384 --> 00:23:41,553
-So in these times…
-Hitting where it hurts.

609
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:43,321
…there are instances where people

610
00:23:43,388 --> 00:23:46,258
would want to drag me down low
to inflict damage on me.

611
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:50,862
What would I get from fighting him?

612
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:52,764
-My gosh.
-That's harsh.

613
00:23:52,831 --> 00:23:55,066
Did amateur baseball
never teach you anything

614
00:23:55,133 --> 00:23:58,637
-about social skills and relationships?
-Where are your social skills?

615
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:01,440
This isn't exactly related,

616
00:24:01,506 --> 00:24:04,242
but we once played baseball together
ten years ago.

617
00:24:04,309 --> 00:24:05,977
-You did?
-Really?

618
00:24:06,044 --> 00:24:08,480
We were going to see
who pitched the ball faster.

619
00:24:08,547 --> 00:24:09,781
It was at Dosan Park.

620
00:24:09,848 --> 00:24:12,083
I just went out in sneakers.

621
00:24:12,150 --> 00:24:15,420
But this guy came out in baseball cleats!

622
00:24:15,487 --> 00:24:17,222
HE WENT THAT FAR?

623
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:19,124
MR. AMATEUR PLAYER IS OVERLY PASSIONATE

624
00:24:19,191 --> 00:24:20,959
What's important now

625
00:24:21,026 --> 00:24:23,028
isn't who was wearing what on that day,

626
00:24:23,094 --> 00:24:25,197
but whose pitch was faster.

627
00:24:25,263 --> 00:24:27,899
THE CHEFS ARE SO SERIOUS ABOUT BASEBALL

628
00:24:27,966 --> 00:24:29,568
But yes, his pitches were fast.

629
00:24:29,634 --> 00:24:31,970
We have a recording
of something Hyun-suk said.

630
00:24:32,037 --> 00:24:35,140
"Sam's vegetable dishes
just taste like grass."

631
00:24:35,207 --> 00:24:37,209
"It only tastes like grass."

632
00:24:37,275 --> 00:24:39,177
THE ELDERS OF THE SHOW
ARE IN A DIRTY FIGHT(?)

633
00:24:39,244 --> 00:24:42,714
-Like the lawn.
-I didn't say it like that.

634
00:24:42,781 --> 00:24:45,317
We must create a different flavor
to let someone overcome picky eating.

635
00:24:45,383 --> 00:24:47,419
But Chef Sam is a naturalist,

636
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:51,056
so I believe he's going to cook something
that brings out the vegetable flavors.

637
00:24:51,122 --> 00:24:55,393
That was why I said it'd taste like grass.

638
00:24:55,460 --> 00:24:57,629
-So he said it.
-It was true.

639
00:24:57,696 --> 00:24:59,431
Thus, Sam can't create a different flavor?

640
00:24:59,498 --> 00:25:00,999
I can.

641
00:25:01,066 --> 00:25:02,434
-He says so.
-I can.

642
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:03,768
-But you don't?
-However,

643
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:06,404
-I want to keep my style.
-It's your style.

644
00:25:06,471 --> 00:25:08,707
Fine. I'm a chef without a style

645
00:25:08,773 --> 00:25:10,542
or social skills.

646
00:25:10,609 --> 00:25:12,677
He's sulking. All right. Fine.

647
00:25:12,744 --> 00:25:15,347
-All I want are stars.
-All right.

648
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:18,250
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS:
EGGPLANT, CARROT, PEANUT BUTTER

649
00:25:18,316 --> 00:25:20,352
CHIVE, YOGURT, MAPLE SYRUP,
LEMON JUICE, MILK, BUTTER, RAMYEON

650
00:25:20,919 --> 00:25:22,888
This is the name of my dish.

651
00:25:22,954 --> 00:25:24,956
Choi Choi Train.

652
00:25:25,023 --> 00:25:26,525
-Choi Choi Train?
-Choi Choi Train.

653
00:25:26,591 --> 00:25:28,293
HE'S CHOO CHOO TRAIN

654
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:30,829
I also didn't like carrots and eggplants.

655
00:25:30,896 --> 00:25:33,565
I didn't like that mushy texture.

656
00:25:33,632 --> 00:25:34,733
YOU'RE RIGHT

657
00:25:34,799 --> 00:25:37,469
I'll change their textures and flavors
and let you overcome

658
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:38,970
your picky eating habits.

659
00:25:39,037 --> 00:25:40,071
And I'll fight head-on.

660
00:25:40,138 --> 00:25:43,208
I'm going to use all three ingredients
that you don't like,

661
00:25:43,275 --> 00:25:44,543
carrots, eggplants, and peanut butter.

662
00:25:45,443 --> 00:25:46,578
All of them?

663
00:25:46,645 --> 00:25:50,315
I'll present the dish
like a French scallop dish

664
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:52,484
-for you to enjoy with your eyes.
-Scallop dish?

665
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:53,852
It'll feel like a different dish.

666
00:25:54,419 --> 00:25:55,887
EXPECTATIONS GOING UP

667
00:25:56,721 --> 00:25:58,790
CHEF SAM'S INGREDIENTS: EGGPLANT,
CARROT, SHRIMP, PORK BELLY, LETTUCE

668
00:25:58,857 --> 00:26:00,892
ESPRESSO CHEESE, PORK CUTLET SAUCE,
LEMON JUICE, MAYO, MUSTARD, BALSAMIC

669
00:26:00,959 --> 00:26:03,295
The dish I'm making is this.

670
00:26:03,361 --> 00:26:05,063
You've Got to Be Eggplanting Me.

671
00:26:05,130 --> 00:26:06,331
CHOI HYUN-SUK?

672
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:07,832
Are you saying that to someone?

673
00:26:07,899 --> 00:26:10,468
-You've got to be kidding me!
-You've Got to Be Eggplanting Me!

674
00:26:10,535 --> 00:26:11,403
You've Got to Be Eggplanting Me?

675
00:26:11,469 --> 00:26:13,271
"Don't brag anymore." Something like that.

676
00:26:13,838 --> 00:26:14,806
A HUGE BLOW

677
00:26:15,273 --> 00:26:16,408
HIS WORDS MADE THE ENTIRE CAST…

678
00:26:16,474 --> 00:26:18,343
-That felt so good!
-My gosh!

679
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:20,545
…AND THE PRODUCTION CREW CHEER

680
00:26:20,612 --> 00:26:22,581
PRODUCTION CREW… EVEN YOU GUYS?

681
00:26:22,647 --> 00:26:24,416
Even the production crew is going crazy.

682
00:26:24,482 --> 00:26:26,718
-That felt good. I wanted to say that.
-It did.

683
00:26:26,785 --> 00:26:28,920
He doesn't like
eggplants and carrots, right?

684
00:26:28,987 --> 00:26:31,122
Because you've worked in America
for a long time,

685
00:26:31,189 --> 00:26:32,257
I'll make a burger

686
00:26:32,324 --> 00:26:34,392
using eggplants as buns.

687
00:26:34,459 --> 00:26:36,728
-A burger?
-And as for the patty,

688
00:26:36,795 --> 00:26:39,564
I'll use shrimp
and your favorite, pork belly.

689
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:41,433
-So that'll be the patty.
-Sounds great.

690
00:26:41,499 --> 00:26:43,868
Lastly, I'll make carrot coleslaw
and add it to the burger.

691
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:47,072
I'll create a familiar flavor
with the ingredients you dislike

692
00:26:47,138 --> 00:26:49,174
so you can enjoy the dish.

693
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:51,309
-Eggplants?
-Eggplant buns?

694
00:26:51,376 --> 00:26:52,243
All right, then.

695
00:26:52,310 --> 00:26:55,146
Let us begin their round.

696
00:26:55,213 --> 00:26:58,049
He's here to prove
why he's keeping first place.

697
00:26:58,116 --> 00:27:01,186
The cooking ghost of the show,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

698
00:27:01,252 --> 00:27:03,555
But this man is determined
to stop his winning streak

699
00:27:03,622 --> 00:27:05,624
and mess him up before the playoffs.

700
00:27:05,690 --> 00:27:07,325
"If I go down, I'm taking you with me."

701
00:27:07,392 --> 00:27:09,461
Chef Sam Kim is up against him.

702
00:27:10,795 --> 00:27:14,232
It's a dirty fight
between the two elders of the show.

703
00:27:16,067 --> 00:27:17,335
-The geezers.
-The elders.

704
00:27:18,370 --> 00:27:19,804
Who'll rise as the winner?

705
00:27:19,871 --> 00:27:23,608
-Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!
-Let's go!

706
00:27:25,243 --> 00:27:26,745
-I'm looking forward to this.
-Okay!

707
00:27:27,312 --> 00:27:29,648
THE DIRTY FIGHT BEGINS

708
00:27:29,714 --> 00:27:32,083
One uses an eggplant,
the other picks up a carrot.

709
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:35,020
There are many people
who don't eat eggplants and carrots.

710
00:27:35,086 --> 00:27:37,355
-There are.
-I can't stand the texture.

711
00:27:37,422 --> 00:27:40,091
-So you mostly don't like the texture?
-No.

712
00:27:40,158 --> 00:27:42,694
Sam cuts eggplants into small pieces.

713
00:27:42,761 --> 00:27:43,828
What are you putting them in?

714
00:27:43,895 --> 00:27:45,363
-Frying powder.
-Frying powder.

715
00:27:45,430 --> 00:27:48,166
-He said he'd make eggplant buns.
-He did.

716
00:27:48,233 --> 00:27:50,969
So how will he make buns
by chopping them up like that?

717
00:27:51,036 --> 00:27:53,271
Will he mash them after deep-frying?

718
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:56,074
I think he'll deep-fry those as is.

719
00:27:56,641 --> 00:27:58,643
STRAIGHT INTO THE OIL!

720
00:27:58,710 --> 00:27:59,944
He just dropped those in.

721
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:02,681
How will he make buns with eggplants?

722
00:28:02,747 --> 00:28:04,349
WHAT ABOUT HYUN-SUK AND THE CARROT?

723
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:08,553
Hyun-suk is slicing the carrot
with a potato peeler.

724
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:10,255
This isn't going to work.

725
00:28:10,321 --> 00:28:11,256
Switch it up.

726
00:28:11,322 --> 00:28:14,225
CHOPPING

727
00:28:14,793 --> 00:28:15,927
WATCH THE 1ST PLACE CHOP

728
00:28:15,994 --> 00:28:18,496
My gosh. He keeps missing the carrot.

729
00:28:18,563 --> 00:28:20,165
That's just like how I do it.

730
00:28:20,231 --> 00:28:23,034
-It was loud, but it was inaccurate.
-He's just like me.

731
00:28:23,101 --> 00:28:24,669
-He is.
-He's no different from me.

732
00:28:24,736 --> 00:28:26,204
Yes, he just made a loud chopping noise.

733
00:28:26,271 --> 00:28:27,672
Stop copying me!

734
00:28:27,739 --> 00:28:28,907
YOU HAVE BETTER PEOPLE TO COPY

735
00:28:29,474 --> 00:28:31,009
THE 1ST PLACE COMPLETELY LOSES HIS FACE

736
00:28:31,076 --> 00:28:32,911
What's next? Salt?

737
00:28:32,977 --> 00:28:34,045
FASTBALLING SALT!

738
00:28:34,713 --> 00:28:35,747
HEY, THERE

739
00:28:36,314 --> 00:28:37,749
LOOK AT YOU

740
00:28:37,816 --> 00:28:39,117
Salt?

741
00:28:39,684 --> 00:28:41,720
HOW'S MY PITCHING FORM?

742
00:28:41,786 --> 00:28:42,987
He has terrible control.

743
00:28:43,054 --> 00:28:44,489
He threw it into all four pots.

744
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:46,424
POTS: I'LL GET SALTY…

745
00:28:46,491 --> 00:28:48,560
His arm didn't come up all the way.

746
00:28:49,127 --> 00:28:51,629
<i>-Did he get all four on purpose?</i>
<i>-He can't raise his arm as high.</i>

747
00:28:51,696 --> 00:28:52,997
<i>Did he want to get all of them?</i>

748
00:28:53,064 --> 00:28:55,166
-What a shame.
-That was a shotgun shot.

749
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:56,401
Next, chives.

750
00:28:56,468 --> 00:28:58,503
-Chives are great for you.
-Yes.

751
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:02,674
-He's boiling the chives.
-I think he's blanching them.

752
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:04,476
He washes them right away.

753
00:29:04,542 --> 00:29:06,277
I think he's making chive oil.

754
00:29:06,344 --> 00:29:08,046
Chive oil?

755
00:29:08,113 --> 00:29:09,481
Right, by blending it?

756
00:29:10,115 --> 00:29:11,850
Shouldn't he have wrung it out harder?

757
00:29:11,916 --> 00:29:13,451
QUICKLY MAKES CHIVE OIL

758
00:29:14,018 --> 00:29:14,953
WHAT ABOUT OUR CHEF SAINT?

759
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:19,023
2. MAKE PATTY BY BLENDING
SHRIMP, PORK BELLY, AND EGGS

760
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:20,859
He's grinding shrimp and pork.

761
00:29:21,359 --> 00:29:23,661
He must be making the patty.

762
00:29:24,162 --> 00:29:25,063
MINCED ONION

763
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:26,664
He's making the patty.

764
00:29:26,731 --> 00:29:28,533
What did you put into the patty?

765
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:31,803
-What's in it?
-Here? Eggs, onion, shrimp,

766
00:29:31,870 --> 00:29:33,404
-Shrimp.
-and some pork cutlet sauce.

767
00:29:33,471 --> 00:29:36,808
Chef Sam always explains so nicely,
no matter how busy he is.

768
00:29:37,375 --> 00:29:38,743
HUFF AND PUFF…

769
00:29:38,810 --> 00:29:40,845
Peanut butter.

770
00:29:40,912 --> 00:29:41,880
-Peanut butter and yogurt.
-That's good.

771
00:29:41,946 --> 00:29:44,182
-That's good.
-It really is.

772
00:29:44,249 --> 00:29:46,785
-And I'll also add some maple syrup.
-That looks good.

773
00:29:47,418 --> 00:29:48,686
-Lastly, lemon juice.
-Lemon juice.

774
00:29:49,454 --> 00:29:51,956
Chef Hyun-suk also explains it nicely.

775
00:29:52,023 --> 00:29:53,992
-Only because Chef Sam did it.
-Yes.

776
00:29:54,058 --> 00:29:56,227
-He had to do it too.
-He had to.

777
00:29:56,895 --> 00:29:58,229
And then what?

778
00:29:58,296 --> 00:29:59,864
-He blended it.
-It's a sauce?

779
00:29:59,931 --> 00:30:02,300
-That's the sauce?
-That has to be good.

780
00:30:02,367 --> 00:30:04,869
It looks like a very delicious dip.

781
00:30:04,936 --> 00:30:06,971
-Fresh yogurt and…
-Peanut butter.

782
00:30:07,572 --> 00:30:09,073
NEXT, THE BLENDER AGAIN

783
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:11,876
-He's grinding <i>ramyeon</i> noodles.
-<i>Ramyeon?</i>

784
00:30:11,943 --> 00:30:13,545
-Chef Hyun-suk uses <i>ramyeon.</i>
<i>-Ramyeon?</i>

785
00:30:13,611 --> 00:30:14,946
-<i>Ramyeon?</i>
-Wait, what?

786
00:30:15,013 --> 00:30:16,114
Is he grinding it?

787
00:30:16,614 --> 00:30:17,849
How will he use that?

788
00:30:18,416 --> 00:30:20,251
Deep-fried eggplants are out.

789
00:30:20,318 --> 00:30:21,586
Deep-fried eggplants are done.

790
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:23,021
-What will he do?
-What now?

791
00:30:23,087 --> 00:30:24,622
How will he make buns?

792
00:30:24,689 --> 00:30:27,325
-Will he deep-fry those again?
-Will he stick them together?

793
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:29,194
Yes, I'll put them back together.

794
00:30:29,260 --> 00:30:30,662
I knew it.

795
00:30:30,728 --> 00:30:32,831
So he deep-fried the pieces on purpose.

796
00:30:32,897 --> 00:30:35,500
-It was to eliminate water.
-You're right.

797
00:30:35,567 --> 00:30:39,070
-Again? He uses a ladle to shape it.
-Just like that?

798
00:30:39,137 --> 00:30:40,471
-I see.
-Whoa.

799
00:30:40,538 --> 00:30:41,706
That's so new.

800
00:30:42,273 --> 00:30:45,410
A CREATIVE APPROACH

801
00:30:45,476 --> 00:30:48,479
-Why didn't you do that sooner?
-Exactly!

802
00:30:48,546 --> 00:30:50,415
-You should've done it long ago.
-No.

803
00:30:50,481 --> 00:30:51,883
You could always do that!

804
00:30:51,950 --> 00:30:54,519
-Sam was a genius too.
-Yes, tell me about it.

805
00:30:54,586 --> 00:30:55,820
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN ELIMINATED!

806
00:30:55,887 --> 00:30:56,855
You can be creative!

807
00:30:56,921 --> 00:30:58,823
"You can be creative"?

808
00:30:59,390 --> 00:31:01,526
A RECIPE YOU'LL WANT TO CHOO-RY

809
00:31:01,593 --> 00:31:03,695
That's a new approach.

810
00:31:03,761 --> 00:31:05,663
He just made the bun.

811
00:31:05,730 --> 00:31:06,931
WHAT NOW? CREATIVITY?

812
00:31:06,998 --> 00:31:09,267
Chef Hyun-suk also grabs an eggplant.

813
00:31:09,334 --> 00:31:10,335
Eggplant.

814
00:31:11,002 --> 00:31:12,403
He's making shapes.

815
00:31:12,470 --> 00:31:14,539
Those will turn out like scallops.

816
00:31:14,606 --> 00:31:16,541
-Scallops?
-They're shaped like scallops.

817
00:31:16,608 --> 00:31:19,677
-Hyun-suk is such a genius.
-That's how he's doing it.

818
00:31:20,245 --> 00:31:21,446
CREATIVITY IS…

819
00:31:21,512 --> 00:31:22,413
MY THING!

820
00:31:25,984 --> 00:31:27,118
He's so serious.

821
00:31:27,185 --> 00:31:28,519
HE SERIOUSLY GOT ANNOYED

822
00:31:28,586 --> 00:31:30,688
I haven't even cooked today.

823
00:31:30,755 --> 00:31:32,390
IT'S A LOT OF FUN FOR THE DUGOUT

824
00:31:32,457 --> 00:31:34,025
Here, instant replay.

825
00:31:34,592 --> 00:31:35,493
YOU CAN'T SEE MY HAND

826
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:36,594
THE 2ND ATTACK

827
00:31:37,328 --> 00:31:38,863
Why is he seasoning us?

828
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:40,932
It's so salty.

829
00:31:40,999 --> 00:31:42,533
GETTING SEASONED…

830
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:44,702
There's salt everywhere.

831
00:31:44,769 --> 00:31:46,271
AFTERMATH OF HIS PERFORMANCE…

832
00:31:46,337 --> 00:31:47,705
It's like a salt pond.

833
00:31:47,772 --> 00:31:50,041
-Will you use that later?
-I should.

834
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:53,111
He's acting out more
in front of his favorite ballplayers.

835
00:31:53,177 --> 00:31:54,612
He's showing off.

836
00:31:55,346 --> 00:31:58,917
That's the bun.
He said it'd be used as the burger bun.

837
00:31:58,983 --> 00:32:02,954
-But the shape still looks mushy now.
-The shape.

838
00:32:03,021 --> 00:32:06,457
-He should make it stay intact.
-It has to be harder, right?

839
00:32:06,524 --> 00:32:09,060
What he doesn't like is the mushy texture.

840
00:32:09,627 --> 00:32:11,095
GRILLING THE EGGPLANT BUN OVER CHEESE!

841
00:32:11,162 --> 00:32:12,497
He's grilling the bun!

842
00:32:12,563 --> 00:32:15,667
-You were going to grill it?
-He's doing something!

843
00:32:15,733 --> 00:32:17,902
-By using cheese?
-He's using cheese.

844
00:32:17,969 --> 00:32:21,439
When you give it a cheese crust,
it'll become crunchy.

845
00:32:21,506 --> 00:32:24,008
-Why didn't you do this before?
-Why didn't you?

846
00:32:24,075 --> 00:32:25,877
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS NOW?

847
00:32:25,944 --> 00:32:27,946
-You could always do this!
-You could!

848
00:32:28,012 --> 00:32:30,381
You're doing this now
at the end of the regular season?

849
00:32:30,448 --> 00:32:32,183
-He's finally doing it.
-How frustrating.

850
00:32:32,250 --> 00:32:34,519
Don't do this in December.
You should've done it earlier.

851
00:32:34,585 --> 00:32:36,287
You should've done it in April.

852
00:32:36,354 --> 00:32:37,422
Yes, since April.

853
00:32:37,488 --> 00:32:39,157
-Come on.
-You could've been

854
00:32:39,223 --> 00:32:42,460
-the first or the second.
-Are you rooting for me or bashing me?

855
00:32:42,527 --> 00:32:44,228
HE'S MAD

856
00:32:45,496 --> 00:32:49,434
NATURE OVER TRENDINESS
TASTINESS OVER NATURE

857
00:32:50,001 --> 00:32:52,403
STARS HAVE LEFT ME BECAUSE I WAS A SAINT

858
00:32:52,470 --> 00:32:55,807
BUT I CAN'T EVEN CRY
DO I NOT HAVE A HEART?

859
00:32:55,873 --> 00:32:57,508
Are you rooting for me or bashing me?

860
00:32:57,575 --> 00:32:59,143
TURNED DARK

861
00:32:59,210 --> 00:33:00,745
We're rooting for you.

862
00:33:00,812 --> 00:33:02,146
-Go, Sam!
-Go, Sam!

863
00:33:02,213 --> 00:33:03,915
GO, SAM

864
00:33:04,482 --> 00:33:05,850
CHUCKLE…

865
00:33:05,917 --> 00:33:07,418
-Go, Sam!
-Go, Sam!

866
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:10,722
Show us your canine teeth!

867
00:33:10,788 --> 00:33:12,957
GRILLING THE PATTY
WHILE SHOWING HIS CANINE TEETH

868
00:33:13,024 --> 00:33:15,193
WHAT ABOUT THE LONELY 1ST PLACE
WITHOUT ANY SUPPORT?

869
00:33:15,793 --> 00:33:18,563
-What did he grind?
-<i>Ramyeon</i> noodles.

870
00:33:18,629 --> 00:33:21,766
-I think he'll use it to deep-fry.
-He's using that as frying batter?

871
00:33:21,833 --> 00:33:23,267
The ground <i>ramyeon</i> noodles?

872
00:33:23,334 --> 00:33:25,670
-He dunked eggplants in it.
-It looks good!

873
00:33:25,737 --> 00:33:27,138
He dips it into the frying batter

874
00:33:27,205 --> 00:33:29,240
and coats it with powdered <i>ramyeon.</i>

875
00:33:29,307 --> 00:33:30,908
He'll deep-fry those after.

876
00:33:30,975 --> 00:33:33,878
THE BESTEST IN CREATIVITY

877
00:33:33,945 --> 00:33:36,180
That's a great idea.

878
00:33:36,247 --> 00:33:39,484
Chef Hyun-suk is in first place because
he has shown creativity since we began.

879
00:33:39,550 --> 00:33:41,686
-Tell me about it.
-That's true.

880
00:33:41,753 --> 00:33:43,855
Poong is going to copy that soon.

881
00:33:43,921 --> 00:33:46,124
-He'll use it.
-He kept a close eye on it.

882
00:33:46,190 --> 00:33:47,592
What's that cheese?

883
00:33:47,658 --> 00:33:49,227
What kind of cheese is that?

884
00:33:49,293 --> 00:33:52,997
It's cheese that has coffee in it.

885
00:33:53,064 --> 00:33:55,066
-Coffee?
-My wife and I enjoy

886
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:57,035
espresso cheese often
with a glass of wine.

887
00:33:57,101 --> 00:33:58,469
A FAVORITE BAR SNACK

888
00:33:58,536 --> 00:34:00,905
-Because you love coffee too.
-I do.

889
00:34:00,972 --> 00:34:02,306
Carrot.

890
00:34:02,373 --> 00:34:03,541
GRATING THE CARROT

891
00:34:03,608 --> 00:34:04,942
-He's doing his best.
-Yes.

892
00:34:06,077 --> 00:34:09,914
3. MIX WITH SALT, LEMON JUICE, MUSTARD,
GROUND PEPPER, MAYO, AND OLIVE OIL

893
00:34:09,981 --> 00:34:11,215
The coleslaw.

894
00:34:11,916 --> 00:34:12,750
Mayonnaise.

895
00:34:13,317 --> 00:34:15,486
4. BURGER SAUCE: MIX MAYO, MUSTARD,
PORK CUTLET SAUCE, LEMON JUICE

896
00:34:15,553 --> 00:34:16,921
He's moving very quickly today.

897
00:34:17,789 --> 00:34:20,591
It looks like Chef Hyun-suk
just turned carrots into purée.

898
00:34:20,658 --> 00:34:22,660
Carrot purée? Will he boil that?

899
00:34:22,727 --> 00:34:25,363
When you purée carrots,
it'll taste like sweet pumpkin.

900
00:34:25,430 --> 00:34:26,731
MAKING CARROT PURÉE

901
00:34:27,298 --> 00:34:28,566
AND WHEN HE SALTS, OF COURSE…

902
00:34:28,633 --> 00:34:29,967
OVERHAND THROW!

903
00:34:30,034 --> 00:34:31,402
You put in too much salt!

904
00:34:32,937 --> 00:34:34,338
HALF OF IT MISSED

905
00:34:34,405 --> 00:34:36,307
-A lot got in this time.
-Yes, you put in too much.

906
00:34:36,374 --> 00:34:38,443
-That was a lot.
-He'll build a salt castle soon.

907
00:34:38,509 --> 00:34:40,311
Look at the amount of salt.

908
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:42,113
Use just that to season your food.

909
00:34:42,180 --> 00:34:43,448
Why is there so much salt?

910
00:34:43,514 --> 00:34:46,250
Please use the salt sparingly, will you?

911
00:34:46,317 --> 00:34:47,151
5 MINUTES!

912
00:34:47,985 --> 00:34:51,055
-Sung-ju, five minutes. Please go.
-Five minutes? Already?

913
00:34:51,122 --> 00:34:53,791
I almost missed it
if Hyun-jin didn't tell me.

914
00:34:53,858 --> 00:34:55,793
-That's him.
-What were you all doing?

915
00:34:55,860 --> 00:34:57,528
The guest had to tell me!

916
00:34:57,595 --> 00:34:59,697
I thought you had become a catcher.

917
00:34:59,764 --> 00:35:01,933
<i>You suddenly gave us a sign.</i>

918
00:35:01,999 --> 00:35:05,770
He's making buns with eggplants right now.

919
00:35:05,837 --> 00:35:06,704
And the patty.

920
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:08,840
He puts a lot of work into the buns.

921
00:35:08,906 --> 00:35:11,642
I hope the buns turn out firm.

922
00:35:11,709 --> 00:35:14,512
Let me check and see how it feels.

923
00:35:14,579 --> 00:35:16,347
-Can it be used as a bun?
-Does it feel hard?

924
00:35:16,414 --> 00:35:18,216
-No, it's not fully cooked.
-It looks like a bun.

925
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:20,451
It's still rather mushy.

926
00:35:20,518 --> 00:35:23,921
Once it's served,
it'll become harder as it cools.

927
00:35:23,988 --> 00:35:25,389
What if you press on it?

928
00:35:25,456 --> 00:35:27,358
Press on it and add more cheese.

929
00:35:27,425 --> 00:35:30,461
-Sam, why don't you press it?
-He keeps adding more cheese.

930
00:35:30,528 --> 00:35:32,230
-Press it hard.
-He keeps adding cheese.

931
00:35:32,296 --> 00:35:33,631
Try as I say.

932
00:35:33,698 --> 00:35:36,067
Poong is trying to teach Sam.

933
00:35:36,134 --> 00:35:39,137
Just press hard on it
and make it crunchier.

934
00:35:39,203 --> 00:35:40,705
Yes, press harder.

935
00:35:40,771 --> 00:35:42,807
Press harder. Be much bolder.

936
00:35:42,874 --> 00:35:44,909
Be quiet.

937
00:35:46,711 --> 00:35:49,614
Yes, he doesn't care
about acting nice anymore!

938
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:51,816
He wasn't like that!

939
00:35:51,883 --> 00:35:53,351
Sam has had enough too.

940
00:35:53,417 --> 00:35:55,119
I'LL SHOW YOU MY MEANER SELF

941
00:35:55,987 --> 00:35:57,588
It's a little burnt.

942
00:35:57,655 --> 00:35:59,524
-I have to burn it.
-Are you burning it?

943
00:35:59,590 --> 00:36:01,259
-Yes.
-He burnt it a little.

944
00:36:01,325 --> 00:36:02,927
OLIVE OIL

945
00:36:03,494 --> 00:36:06,297
5. MIX OLIVE OIL, BALSAMIC DRESSING,
GROUND PEPPER, MUSTARD, AND LETTUCE

946
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:08,266
They're rivals with history.

947
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:10,935
Choi Hyun-suk versus Sam Kim,
Sam Kim versus Choi Hyun-suk.

948
00:36:11,002 --> 00:36:12,236
1ST PLACE, HYUN-SUK, WIDENS THE GAP

949
00:36:12,303 --> 00:36:14,205
What did you say these were?

950
00:36:14,672 --> 00:36:15,940
DOUBLE FRYING TO ADD CRUNCHINESS

951
00:36:16,007 --> 00:36:17,041
He puts them back in.

952
00:36:17,675 --> 00:36:19,744
Carrot purée.

953
00:36:19,810 --> 00:36:21,612
BLENDING CARROT PURÉE IN A BLENDER!

954
00:36:21,679 --> 00:36:23,481
-The purée is ready.
-The purée.

955
00:36:23,548 --> 00:36:26,017
-The purée looks great!
-Does it?

956
00:36:26,083 --> 00:36:27,585
My gosh. Oh, my!

957
00:36:27,652 --> 00:36:30,922
No one can make purée like that
in 15 minutes.

958
00:36:30,988 --> 00:36:33,691
-You can't make it that smooth.
-Hyun-suk!

959
00:36:33,758 --> 00:36:36,594
Look at how he's in command!

960
00:36:36,661 --> 00:36:40,064
Hyun-suk is doing his best today
for the two ballplayers he respects.

961
00:36:40,131 --> 00:36:41,732
-Will you serve it now?
-Two minutes.

962
00:36:41,799 --> 00:36:43,935
-Two minutes.
-About two minutes left.

963
00:36:44,001 --> 00:36:46,204
-Two minutes left.
-Two minutes.

964
00:36:46,270 --> 00:36:49,473
-That looks good.
-Wait, more cheese?

965
00:36:49,540 --> 00:36:51,409
He keeps adding more cheese!

966
00:36:51,475 --> 00:36:54,011
-That's too much cheese.
-Are these cheese buns?

967
00:36:54,078 --> 00:36:55,746
He's using too much cheese.

968
00:36:55,813 --> 00:36:58,816
-It won't taste like eggplant.
-It won't.

969
00:36:58,883 --> 00:37:00,818
Shin-soo just said
you're using too much cheese.

970
00:37:01,652 --> 00:37:04,288
He's trying to cover
all the eggplants with cheese!

971
00:37:04,355 --> 00:37:06,924
But eggplants always go well with cheese.

972
00:37:06,991 --> 00:37:09,026
-Is that so?
-Like eggplant parmigiana.

973
00:37:09,093 --> 00:37:11,862
Hyun-suk is moving very quickly.
He's almost finished.

974
00:37:11,929 --> 00:37:13,798
SPREAD THE CARROT PURÉE FIRST

975
00:37:13,864 --> 00:37:15,866
-Peanut butter.
-That looks good.

976
00:37:15,933 --> 00:37:16,968
6. ADD MAPLE SYRUP TO SAUCE

977
00:37:17,034 --> 00:37:18,536
It's the fine dining style.

978
00:37:18,603 --> 00:37:19,704
FINISHING WITH SALT!

979
00:37:19,770 --> 00:37:21,005
Maple syrup. Whoa!

980
00:37:21,072 --> 00:37:22,406
WATCH OUT FOR A FOUL BALL

981
00:37:22,974 --> 00:37:25,309
THE PEANUT SAUCE GOES INTO THE MOLD!

982
00:37:25,376 --> 00:37:28,479
Look at how focused Hyun-suk is.

983
00:37:28,546 --> 00:37:30,414
See how focused he is from below.

984
00:37:30,481 --> 00:37:31,749
CAMERAWORK FROM THE '80S

985
00:37:31,816 --> 00:37:33,384
THE CUTTING BOARD POV

986
00:37:33,451 --> 00:37:35,653
AND THE PASSIONATE CAMERAMAN…

987
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:38,055
It's as if he's making a piece of art.

988
00:37:38,122 --> 00:37:40,725
My gosh. Look at that,
now that he has removed the mold.

989
00:37:40,791 --> 00:37:42,660
Exactly three pieces.

990
00:37:42,727 --> 00:37:44,962
Are you done, Hyun-suk? He is!

991
00:37:45,029 --> 00:37:46,564
Hyun-suk is done.

992
00:37:46,631 --> 00:37:48,699
A nifty finish.

993
00:37:48,766 --> 00:37:50,268
-No way.
-Fifty seconds.

994
00:37:50,334 --> 00:37:54,305
Fifty seconds. It's now Sam's time.

995
00:37:54,372 --> 00:37:55,840
The burger.

996
00:37:55,906 --> 00:37:57,975
And on top, the lettuce.

997
00:37:58,042 --> 00:37:59,110
WHAT'S UP NEXT?

998
00:37:59,176 --> 00:38:02,847
Eggplants, which he hates.
He seasoned them a little and…

999
00:38:02,913 --> 00:38:04,315
-Carrots.
-Yes, carrots.

1000
00:38:04,882 --> 00:38:05,916
SO BLATANTLY CARROTS

1001
00:38:05,983 --> 00:38:07,518
Your taste and vision are all gone!

1002
00:38:07,585 --> 00:38:10,454
-He seasoned carrots and topped the patty.
-Both your taste and vision!

1003
00:38:10,521 --> 00:38:12,423
-The eggplant bun!
-The eggplant bun.

1004
00:38:12,490 --> 00:38:14,625
-It looks good.
-I've never seen orange eggplants.

1005
00:38:15,192 --> 00:38:18,596
-Wait, no!
-Why did you cut it?

1006
00:38:18,663 --> 00:38:21,332
-It's fine.
-You shouldn't have cut it.

1007
00:38:21,399 --> 00:38:23,067
You're throwing your last round!

1008
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:24,669
-I'm not.
-Twenty seconds.

1009
00:38:24,735 --> 00:38:27,805
-He had to put the sauce in the middle.
-Right, the sauce.

1010
00:38:27,872 --> 00:38:29,473
-He had a reason.
-He had to cut it.

1011
00:38:29,540 --> 00:38:31,309
Your time's almost up.

1012
00:38:31,375 --> 00:38:33,844
-Ten seconds, Sam!
-Nine. Eight.

1013
00:38:33,911 --> 00:38:36,147
You're not in last place,
you're here to fight me!

1014
00:38:36,213 --> 00:38:38,182
-You can do it! Go! Go, Sam!
-Four.

1015
00:38:38,249 --> 00:38:40,017
-Three. Two.
-Keep it up!

1016
00:38:40,084 --> 00:38:41,252
-One.
-One.

1017
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:42,987
Sam finishes.

1018
00:38:43,054 --> 00:38:44,689
AMAZED

1019
00:38:44,755 --> 00:38:46,324
Both Hyun-suk and Sam are done.

1020
00:38:46,891 --> 00:38:49,026
TAKING OFF QUICKLY LIKE HYUN-JIN'S PITCHES

1021
00:38:49,694 --> 00:38:51,829
HIGH EXPECTATIONS

1022
00:38:51,896 --> 00:38:54,298
And now, both dishes
were finished for Shin-soo,

1023
00:38:54,365 --> 00:38:57,468
who Want Choo Overcome Picky Eating.

1024
00:38:57,535 --> 00:39:00,738
First, please try Chef Hyun-suk's dish,
Choi Choi Train.

1025
00:39:02,506 --> 00:39:05,543
EGGPLANTS DEEP-FRIED IN SCALLOP SHAPES

1026
00:39:06,777 --> 00:39:11,048
FINISHED WITH SPLASHES
OF PEANUT BUTTER SAUCE AND CARROT PURÉE

1027
00:39:12,450 --> 00:39:16,153
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S CHOI CHOI TRAIN

1028
00:39:16,220 --> 00:39:19,724
-What's the yellow?
-The yellow is made with carrots,

1029
00:39:19,790 --> 00:39:22,026
the circular discs are eggplants,

1030
00:39:22,093 --> 00:39:23,728
served with peanut butter sauce.

1031
00:39:23,794 --> 00:39:25,029
I also threw in chive oil.

1032
00:39:25,096 --> 00:39:27,098
You can scoop up everything you see.

1033
00:39:27,164 --> 00:39:29,066
-He's about to try it.
-Gosh.

1034
00:39:29,133 --> 00:39:31,869
Choo Choo Train,
who dislikes eggplants and carrots.

1035
00:39:31,936 --> 00:39:34,472
He said he didn't like the textures.

1036
00:39:34,538 --> 00:39:36,374
Has Hyun-suk changed those?

1037
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:38,042
His wife is probably watching at home.

1038
00:39:38,109 --> 00:39:39,877
It really looks like a scallop.

1039
00:39:41,712 --> 00:39:42,913
FINALLY A BITE

1040
00:39:42,980 --> 00:39:46,050
He's eating eggplant
and carrot at the same time.

1041
00:39:46,117 --> 00:39:48,018
If it tastes like scallops
instead of eggplants,

1042
00:39:48,085 --> 00:39:50,087
that will be unbelievably awesome.

1043
00:39:50,154 --> 00:39:51,922
Texture is also an important part.

1044
00:39:51,989 --> 00:39:53,023
NO RESPONSE?

1045
00:39:53,090 --> 00:39:54,091
He isn't responding yet.

1046
00:39:54,658 --> 00:39:55,960
NERVOUS

1047
00:39:56,026 --> 00:39:58,763
He's not smiling.

1048
00:39:58,829 --> 00:40:01,999
-Does it taste like raw eggplant?
-No way.

1049
00:40:03,100 --> 00:40:05,669
ANOTHER BITE

1050
00:40:08,305 --> 00:40:09,874
WHAT'S GOING ON?

1051
00:40:09,940 --> 00:40:12,977
He looks like a judge
for a cooking competition.

1052
00:40:13,043 --> 00:40:14,812
-What's it like?
-Yes.

1053
00:40:14,879 --> 00:40:17,782
I haven't had too many fine dishes
like this before,

1054
00:40:17,848 --> 00:40:19,383
so I didn't know how to verbalize this.

1055
00:40:19,450 --> 00:40:20,885
Is it far from eggplants?

1056
00:40:20,951 --> 00:40:23,287
-It doesn't taste like eggplants,
-Really?

1057
00:40:23,354 --> 00:40:24,288
including the texture.

1058
00:40:24,855 --> 00:40:26,123
SMILE

1059
00:40:26,190 --> 00:40:27,224
When I chewed it

1060
00:40:27,291 --> 00:40:29,527
twice, three times,
it felt like a sweet potato.

1061
00:40:29,593 --> 00:40:31,328
-Really?
-Sweet potato?

1062
00:40:31,395 --> 00:40:32,563
-The texture?
-Yes.

1063
00:40:32,630 --> 00:40:34,965
<i>He removed the eggplant skin, right?</i>

1064
00:40:35,032 --> 00:40:36,801
<i>-That might have been the reason.</i>
<i>-I guess so.</i>

1065
00:40:36,867 --> 00:40:38,536
It even tastes like sweet potato.

1066
00:40:38,602 --> 00:40:40,504
-Because of carrots.
-But nothing like eggplants.

1067
00:40:40,571 --> 00:40:44,275
<i>It could taste like sweet potato</i>
<i>once it mixes with the sauce.</i>

1068
00:40:44,341 --> 00:40:46,811
<i>-Because it was mixed with carrots.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

1069
00:40:46,877 --> 00:40:50,347
And this peanut butter sauce

1070
00:40:50,414 --> 00:40:53,317
doesn't taste anything like peanuts.

1071
00:40:54,018 --> 00:40:56,554
Also, the eggplant
had been fried to perfection.

1072
00:40:56,620 --> 00:40:57,455
It's crunchy.

1073
00:40:57,521 --> 00:41:00,357
If no one told me,

1074
00:41:00,424 --> 00:41:02,893
I wouldn't have noticed
that the dish was made

1075
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:05,396
<i>with three ingredients I like the least.</i>

1076
00:41:05,463 --> 00:41:09,200
So he did succeed
in hiding the flavors and textures.

1077
00:41:09,266 --> 00:41:10,601
Is the flavor well-balanced?

1078
00:41:12,369 --> 00:41:13,571
LOOKS

1079
00:41:14,138 --> 00:41:15,039
CHUCKLES

1080
00:41:15,105 --> 00:41:17,608
-It has to be delicious.
-Yes, that's what's important.

1081
00:41:17,675 --> 00:41:20,578
-The way he hid it gets 100 points.
-That's 100 points.

1082
00:41:20,644 --> 00:41:21,879
He has hidden them well.

1083
00:41:21,946 --> 00:41:24,715
-He didn't taste or feel the ingredients.
-Yes, that's right.

1084
00:41:24,782 --> 00:41:27,318
But it does taste a bit bland.

1085
00:41:28,285 --> 00:41:30,354
He was too busy hiding everything!

1086
00:41:30,921 --> 00:41:32,523
KIM POONG, YOU!

1087
00:41:32,590 --> 00:41:33,824
He only hid them.

1088
00:41:33,891 --> 00:41:36,193
<i>-He salted the table!</i>
<i>-You used so much salt!</i>

1089
00:41:36,260 --> 00:41:38,896
<i>-Why did you season us?</i>
<i>-It's like a salt pond here.</i>

1090
00:41:39,597 --> 00:41:42,166
-This much salt would've been perfect.
-That's a lot.

1091
00:41:42,233 --> 00:41:45,169
-That would've seasoned it perfectly.
-It would have.

1092
00:41:45,236 --> 00:41:47,538
What did you learn from amateur baseball?

1093
00:41:47,605 --> 00:41:50,107
Speed wasn't the important thing
for pitchers.

1094
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:51,942
I guess it's all about the control.

1095
00:41:52,743 --> 00:41:54,845
-It is.
-It has to get inside first.

1096
00:41:54,912 --> 00:41:56,447
It has to be in the strike zone first.

1097
00:41:56,514 --> 00:41:57,715
Is it a bit bland?

1098
00:41:57,781 --> 00:42:00,651
-Yes, it's quite bland.
-Quite bland?

1099
00:42:00,718 --> 00:42:03,787
I'm not sure how he'll decide,
but you successfully hid everything.

1100
00:42:03,854 --> 00:42:04,688
-He did.
-Okay.

1101
00:42:04,755 --> 00:42:07,258
Next, You've Got to Be Eggplanting Me.

1102
00:42:07,324 --> 00:42:09,360
YOU'VE GOT TO STOP EATING PICKY

1103
00:42:11,695 --> 00:42:15,833
A BURGER MADE WITH EGGPLANT AND CARROT

1104
00:42:18,769 --> 00:42:22,406
CHEF SAM KIM'S
YOU'VE GOT TO BE EGGPLANTING ME

1105
00:42:22,473 --> 00:42:24,909
We can even see
that you were unable to hide them.

1106
00:42:24,975 --> 00:42:27,745
-Yes.
-You can see the eggplant and carrot.

1107
00:42:27,811 --> 00:42:30,381
-But what does it taste like?
-It's crunchy.

1108
00:42:30,447 --> 00:42:32,316
-Please try it.
-The flavor is the problem.

1109
00:42:32,383 --> 00:42:33,851
He tries the patty and the bun.

1110
00:42:33,918 --> 00:42:35,986
The carrot just sits on top.

1111
00:42:36,053 --> 00:42:38,889
He can obviously see
the eggplant and carrot.

1112
00:42:38,956 --> 00:42:40,157
But as long as it's delicious…

1113
00:42:40,224 --> 00:42:42,726
Yes, he's in this fight
just for the taste.

1114
00:42:42,793 --> 00:42:44,128
Is this bland too?

1115
00:42:44,194 --> 00:42:45,162
GETTING EVEN MORE CURIOUS

1116
00:42:45,229 --> 00:42:46,630
Will the train go choo choo?

1117
00:42:47,665 --> 00:42:49,433
QUIETLY TAKES ANOTHER BITE

1118
00:42:49,500 --> 00:42:50,534
First, a quick stop.

1119
00:42:50,601 --> 00:42:52,469
He made a quick stop.

1120
00:42:52,536 --> 00:42:54,939
CHOO CHOO TRAIN STOPS BRIEFLY FOR A MOMENT

1121
00:42:55,005 --> 00:42:56,807
He stops and checks again.

1122
00:42:56,874 --> 00:42:59,276
I wonder what the texture is like.
That's what he hates.

1123
00:43:00,744 --> 00:43:03,914
He's eating this one
after seeing the vegetables.

1124
00:43:03,981 --> 00:43:05,382
And he nods.

1125
00:43:05,883 --> 00:43:07,585
WHAT DOES HE MEAN BY THAT?

1126
00:43:07,651 --> 00:43:09,420
He couldn't hide these visually,

1127
00:43:09,486 --> 00:43:12,723
-but he hid all of their flavors.
-The flavors?

1128
00:43:12,790 --> 00:43:15,092
It tastes special.

1129
00:43:15,159 --> 00:43:16,860
CHOO CHOO TRAIN WANTS TO TAKE OFF!

1130
00:43:16,927 --> 00:43:18,128
<i>That means…</i>

1131
00:43:18,195 --> 00:43:22,066
I can obviously see that
this is eggplant and this is carrot,

1132
00:43:22,132 --> 00:43:25,135
but I couldn't feel it in the texture.

1133
00:43:25,202 --> 00:43:29,607
-Was the patty made with shrimp?
-Yes, you're right.

1134
00:43:29,673 --> 00:43:32,042
At first, visually,

1135
00:43:32,109 --> 00:43:35,079
I thought it looked way too healthy,

1136
00:43:35,145 --> 00:43:36,680
but then, I chewed on some meat.

1137
00:43:36,747 --> 00:43:38,449
The sauce was nice too.

1138
00:43:38,515 --> 00:43:39,984
Did you use mustard?

1139
00:43:40,050 --> 00:43:41,385
Yes, I did.

1140
00:43:41,452 --> 00:43:43,887
Everything went so well with the sauce.

1141
00:43:43,954 --> 00:43:45,856
He used lots of your favorite cheese.

1142
00:43:45,923 --> 00:43:48,125
-I couldn't taste it at all.
-Not at all?

1143
00:43:48,192 --> 00:43:50,894
-Doesn't that mean he wasted it?
-What a waste.

1144
00:43:51,729 --> 00:43:55,232
I used the cheese
because he didn't like eggplant's texture.

1145
00:43:55,299 --> 00:43:57,735
<i>-Was it for the texture?</i>
<i>-I wanted to stick it on the eggplant.</i>

1146
00:43:57,801 --> 00:43:59,670
<i>He did that to hide the eggplant.</i>

1147
00:43:59,737 --> 00:44:01,271
But it doesn't taste like cheese.

1148
00:44:01,338 --> 00:44:04,441
Hyun-jin will try some now.

1149
00:44:04,508 --> 00:44:05,509
So?

1150
00:44:05,576 --> 00:44:06,977
A BIG BITE

1151
00:44:07,044 --> 00:44:09,146
-It looks so pretty.
-It does.

1152
00:44:09,213 --> 00:44:10,748
The presentation is like art.

1153
00:44:12,016 --> 00:44:13,584
-Hmm?
-Hmm?

1154
00:44:14,118 --> 00:44:16,854
I like how light the flavor is.

1155
00:44:17,755 --> 00:44:18,722
BOWS THE 2ND TIME

1156
00:44:18,789 --> 00:44:20,591
-Do you like the light flavor?
-Yes.

1157
00:44:20,658 --> 00:44:21,925
He said it was bland.

1158
00:44:21,992 --> 00:44:23,994
I don't think it's that bland.

1159
00:44:24,061 --> 00:44:25,729
THAT COULD BE THE CASE

1160
00:44:26,597 --> 00:44:27,431
May I finish this?

1161
00:44:27,498 --> 00:44:29,600
-Go ahead.
-He must like it.

1162
00:44:29,667 --> 00:44:31,535
-He really likes deep-fried food.
-They're fried.

1163
00:44:31,602 --> 00:44:33,937
-Yes, they're fried.
-Maybe that's why.

1164
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:35,272
They're deep-fried.

1165
00:44:35,339 --> 00:44:36,440
FINISHING THE LAST 1

1166
00:44:36,507 --> 00:44:38,509
He's eating another deep-fried dish.

1167
00:44:38,575 --> 00:44:40,811
Their responses were completely different.

1168
00:44:40,878 --> 00:44:43,147
-I like it.
-You do?

1169
00:44:43,213 --> 00:44:45,616
-I see. Okay.
-Yes.

1170
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:48,318
Next, Chef Sam's dish.

1171
00:44:48,385 --> 00:44:50,454
-He cuts a huge piece.
-It's a huge bite.

1172
00:44:50,954 --> 00:44:52,089
STUFFING

1173
00:44:52,156 --> 00:44:54,825
Your mouth
is much smaller than I expected.

1174
00:44:54,892 --> 00:44:55,759
It's tiny on the inside.

1175
00:44:58,128 --> 00:44:59,396
GLARING

1176
00:44:59,463 --> 00:45:00,297
He's glaring at it.

1177
00:45:00,364 --> 00:45:03,133
It feels like he has psychokinetic power.

1178
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:04,268
"Rise."

1179
00:45:04,334 --> 00:45:06,003
WHY ARE YOU GLARING AT IT?

1180
00:45:06,070 --> 00:45:09,640
I can't smell or taste the veggies.

1181
00:45:09,707 --> 00:45:11,608
But personally,

1182
00:45:11,675 --> 00:45:13,010
the mustard sauce

1183
00:45:14,311 --> 00:45:17,081
-was a bit too strong.
-Rather?

1184
00:45:17,147 --> 00:45:19,750
He said the first dish was perfect,
while it was bland for Shin-soo.

1185
00:45:19,817 --> 00:45:22,252
And the mustard sauce
was a bit too strong for Hyun-jin.

1186
00:45:22,319 --> 00:45:24,988
Everyone has different tastes.

1187
00:45:25,055 --> 00:45:28,258
-And now, the moment of truth.
-So?

1188
00:45:28,325 --> 00:45:30,928
The fridge owner will make the decision.

1189
00:45:30,994 --> 00:45:32,830
<i>Press one to choose Sam Kim.</i>

1190
00:45:33,731 --> 00:45:35,065
<i>Press two for Choi Hyun-suk.</i>

1191
00:45:36,300 --> 00:45:38,602
Which one of them will
stop his picky eating habit

1192
00:45:38,669 --> 00:45:42,005
and make him eat
eggplant and carrot from now on?

1193
00:45:42,806 --> 00:45:44,074
-Did you press it?
-Yes.

1194
00:45:44,141 --> 00:45:45,476
He did. He made his decision.

1195
00:45:46,043 --> 00:45:47,478
WHOSE SIDE DID HE TAKE?

1196
00:45:47,544 --> 00:45:50,547
Let's find out who he chose! Show us!

1197
00:45:51,448 --> 00:45:53,317
Want Choo Overcome Picky Eating.

1198
00:45:53,383 --> 00:45:56,820
Which one of them made him stop
his picky eating habit?

1199
00:45:56,887 --> 00:45:58,655
Is it Hyun-suk, the sole first place?

1200
00:45:58,722 --> 00:46:01,925
Or is it Sam, the strong player
with a long history?

1201
00:46:02,793 --> 00:46:04,194
Who did he choose?

1202
00:46:04,728 --> 00:46:06,029
What's the result?

1203
00:46:06,864 --> 00:46:09,032
Show us the winner!

1204
00:46:09,099 --> 00:46:11,235
-It was Sam!
-Sam Kim!

1205
00:46:11,301 --> 00:46:13,771
CHEF SAM KIM'S
YOU'VE GOT TO BE EGGPLANTING ME

1206
00:46:14,538 --> 00:46:16,740
PLAYING THE SPOILER AGAINST THE 1ST PLACE

1207
00:46:16,807 --> 00:46:18,342
Sam Sam Train!

1208
00:46:18,408 --> 00:46:19,777
Sam Sam Train wins!

1209
00:46:19,843 --> 00:46:21,445
He should've done this long ago.

1210
00:46:22,746 --> 00:46:24,648
I'LL DO THAT IN THE NEXT YEAR'S SEASON

1211
00:46:24,715 --> 00:46:26,483
I chose something

1212
00:46:26,550 --> 00:46:29,153
that would be easier for my wife to make.

1213
00:46:29,219 --> 00:46:31,221
Thinking about his wife
made the decision easy.

1214
00:46:31,288 --> 00:46:33,524
My children also do not like
eggplants or carrots.

1215
00:46:33,590 --> 00:46:36,126
<i>And when we eat as a family,</i>

1216
00:46:36,193 --> 00:46:38,228
<i>she has to make a lot of food at once.</i>

1217
00:46:38,295 --> 00:46:41,265
Chef Hyun-suk's recipe
seemed to require a lot of work,

1218
00:46:41,331 --> 00:46:43,767
and it seemed much harder

1219
00:46:43,834 --> 00:46:45,235
-to make a huge batch.
-That's true.

1220
00:46:45,302 --> 00:46:48,572
I had to think which dish
we could enjoy with our kids,

1221
00:46:48,639 --> 00:46:50,841
-so I chose Chef Sam's dish.
-I see.

1222
00:46:50,908 --> 00:46:52,075
Do you want to eat that again?

1223
00:46:52,142 --> 00:46:54,144
-I would even go out and eat it.
-You would?

1224
00:46:54,678 --> 00:46:56,413
-He would go out and buy it.
-Game over.

1225
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:58,549
I cannot make it to the championship,

1226
00:46:58,615 --> 00:47:02,052
but just like Shin-soo, who made his way
into the MLB from the Minor League,

1227
00:47:02,119 --> 00:47:04,621
I'll try harder next year
and make the championship then.

1228
00:47:04,688 --> 00:47:06,023
-All right!
-Okay!

1229
00:47:06,089 --> 00:47:07,457
WILL BECOME SHIN-SOO AMONG CHEFS

1230
00:47:07,524 --> 00:47:09,960
-The Choo Shin-soo among chefs!
-Even a great speech.

1231
00:47:10,027 --> 00:47:12,262
Chef Sam gets another star.

1232
00:47:12,329 --> 00:47:15,666
The powerhouse with history,
Sam Kim takes this round. Congratulations!

1233
00:47:15,732 --> 00:47:17,835
He receives a star from Choo Choo Train!

1234
00:47:17,901 --> 00:47:19,603
-Thank you for the dish.
-Thank you.

1235
00:47:19,670 --> 00:47:21,104
WE HOPE YOU BECOME LIKE SHIN-SOO…

1236
00:47:21,171 --> 00:47:25,576
<i>This is the second cook-off</i>
<i>played with Shin-soo's ingredients.</i>

1237
00:47:25,642 --> 00:47:28,645
The lover boy in the world of baseball
wants a seafood bar snack

1238
00:47:28,712 --> 00:47:31,815
he can enjoy over a drink with his wife.

1239
00:47:31,882 --> 00:47:33,884
The romanticist of <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>

1240
00:47:33,951 --> 00:47:36,186
Chef Son Jong-won, is up.

1241
00:47:36,253 --> 00:47:37,955
The dancing artist of <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>

1242
00:47:38,021 --> 00:47:41,458
Chef Jung Ho-young, is also up.

1243
00:47:42,459 --> 00:47:44,328
The dan-tist.

1244
00:47:44,394 --> 00:47:48,031
This is the last regular game
of the 2025 season.

1245
00:47:48,098 --> 00:47:49,533
This is your last showdown.

1246
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:53,804
And this match will bring about
a big change in the ranking.

1247
00:47:53,871 --> 00:47:56,440
<i>-The winner rises to second place.</i>
<i>-Loser, fifth.</i>

1248
00:47:56,506 --> 00:47:59,109
<i>-But the loser becomes fifth place.</i>
<i>-You're right.</i>

1249
00:47:59,176 --> 00:48:00,544
It's a huge difference.

1250
00:48:00,611 --> 00:48:02,112
-That's huge.
-Win, second. Lose, fifth.

1251
00:48:02,179 --> 00:48:03,647
-That's big.
-It's a huge difference.

1252
00:48:03,714 --> 00:48:05,148
Yes, the difference is severe.

1253
00:48:05,215 --> 00:48:09,753
In this season, you two had two cook-offs,
and Chef Jong-won won both times.

1254
00:48:09,820 --> 00:48:11,021
SON JONG-WON 2 : 0 JUNG HO-YOUNG

1255
00:48:11,088 --> 00:48:13,490
And on top of that,

1256
00:48:13,557 --> 00:48:16,593
Chef Ho-young has been suffering
from a three-match losing streak.

1257
00:48:16,660 --> 00:48:17,728
Goodness, my master.

1258
00:48:17,794 --> 00:48:19,363
What will you do now?

1259
00:48:19,429 --> 00:48:21,164
Chef Jong-won said something like this.

1260
00:48:21,231 --> 00:48:22,099
What?

1261
00:48:22,165 --> 00:48:23,800
-There's a recording.
-What is it?

1262
00:48:23,867 --> 00:48:26,436
"Ho-young? He's just a stepping stone."

1263
00:48:28,405 --> 00:48:30,607
ALLOW ME TO WALK OVER

1264
00:48:30,674 --> 00:48:32,509
GETTING INTERESTING

1265
00:48:32,576 --> 00:48:36,914
He wants to trample all over him
and run up to put Hyun-suk down.

1266
00:48:36,980 --> 00:48:40,050
-He's nothing but a bridge.
-He's a bridge.

1267
00:48:40,117 --> 00:48:41,251
He's about to cry.

1268
00:48:41,318 --> 00:48:44,922
Everyone knows
that Chef Ho-young is a talented chef.

1269
00:48:44,988 --> 00:48:46,423
But I analyzed the patterns.

1270
00:48:47,691 --> 00:48:50,694
Know thy enemy, they say.
You analyzed his patterns?

1271
00:48:50,761 --> 00:48:52,796
Whenever he loses,

1272
00:48:52,863 --> 00:48:54,498
his dances are never good.

1273
00:48:55,966 --> 00:48:58,435
-His dance?
-When his dance doesn't go well?

1274
00:48:58,502 --> 00:48:59,670
-When people aren't excited?
-Right.

1275
00:48:59,736 --> 00:49:00,771
The dance is the real thing.

1276
00:49:00,837 --> 00:49:03,607
And I don't think he can top
Chef Eun-yeong's performance.

1277
00:49:04,841 --> 00:49:06,944
Kim Poong, Strikeout!

1278
00:49:07,010 --> 00:49:09,313
I CAME TO WATCH THE STRIKEOUT
LOL CHEF EUN-YEONG IS THE BEST

1279
00:49:09,379 --> 00:49:11,648
THE FEMALE SUNG-JUN, CRAZY ABOUT TV
KIM POONG! STRIKEOUT! LOL

1280
00:49:11,715 --> 00:49:12,816
What did she do?

1281
00:49:12,883 --> 00:49:13,951
There's a lot of pressure.

1282
00:49:14,017 --> 00:49:15,552
-That's tough to beat.
-It was funny.

1283
00:49:15,619 --> 00:49:18,755
She already made everyone laugh,
so it has to be better than that.

1284
00:49:18,822 --> 00:49:21,358
I kept running into him
out in the hallway,

1285
00:49:21,425 --> 00:49:24,461
and he looked quite troubled out there.

1286
00:49:24,528 --> 00:49:27,664
Well, Chef Eun-yeong
killed my spirit completely

1287
00:49:27,731 --> 00:49:28,999
in the previous episode.

1288
00:49:29,566 --> 00:49:30,500
MAXED OUT ON PRESSURE

1289
00:49:30,567 --> 00:49:31,435
His will to fight.

1290
00:49:31,501 --> 00:49:33,036
That's way too hard to beat.

1291
00:49:33,870 --> 00:49:35,906
CHEF JONG-WON'S INGREDIENTS:
SMOKED SALMON, RAW SALMON, AVOCADO

1292
00:49:35,973 --> 00:49:38,008
AVOCADO OIL, CAPER, CHIVE, LEMON,
SALAD GREENS, HORSERADISH, AND MORE

1293
00:49:38,075 --> 00:49:39,843
The dish I'll make is called

1294
00:49:39,910 --> 00:49:41,979
RomantisChoo.

1295
00:49:42,045 --> 00:49:43,780
-RomantisChoo.
-RomantisChoo.

1296
00:49:43,847 --> 00:49:46,616
-Romanticist? RomantisChoo.
-Choo.

1297
00:49:46,683 --> 00:49:49,653
I'll make two different dishes
using salmon.

1298
00:49:49,720 --> 00:49:51,421
First, I'll use smoked salmon

1299
00:49:51,488 --> 00:49:53,423
to make carpaccio,

1300
00:49:53,490 --> 00:49:55,759
and the next dish

1301
00:49:55,826 --> 00:49:59,096
is something romantic you can eat
over a glass of wine with your wife,

1302
00:49:59,162 --> 00:50:01,865
-salmon steak.
-Salmon steak.

1303
00:50:01,932 --> 00:50:03,300
I'd also like to give you tips

1304
00:50:03,367 --> 00:50:05,802
-so that you could make it for her.
-That would be great.

1305
00:50:05,869 --> 00:50:07,104
He'll even give you tips.

1306
00:50:07,170 --> 00:50:08,572
The dish will remind you

1307
00:50:08,638 --> 00:50:11,074
of your wife
more than yourself when you eat it.

1308
00:50:11,641 --> 00:50:12,743
THE LOVER BOY LOVES IT

1309
00:50:12,809 --> 00:50:15,946
If he tries to make it
and finds it too hard,

1310
00:50:16,013 --> 00:50:17,414
can you go over and help him?

1311
00:50:17,481 --> 00:50:21,218
Actually, my uncle lives in Texas.

1312
00:50:21,284 --> 00:50:22,853
I can stop by on my way there.

1313
00:50:22,919 --> 00:50:24,654
-His uncle is there.
-His uncle.

1314
00:50:24,721 --> 00:50:25,889
Using regionalism.

1315
00:50:25,956 --> 00:50:28,058
Well, it's the truth.
Ho-young looks anxious.

1316
00:50:28,125 --> 00:50:29,860
It's an uneven playing field.

1317
00:50:30,360 --> 00:50:32,162
I'll be the butler.

1318
00:50:32,863 --> 00:50:34,197
You look like one.

1319
00:50:34,264 --> 00:50:35,699
Things are heating up.

1320
00:50:35,766 --> 00:50:36,700
-Whoa.
-Whoa.

1321
00:50:36,767 --> 00:50:38,402
He wouldn't open the door.

1322
00:50:38,468 --> 00:50:40,170
The homeowner doesn't want that.

1323
00:50:41,004 --> 00:50:43,073
CHEF HO-YOUNG'S INGREDIENTS:
MUSSEL, SURF CLAM, BIGFIN REEF SQUID

1324
00:50:43,140 --> 00:50:45,175
SCALLOP, SHRIMP, SOYBEAN PULP,
CHERRY TOMATO, PEPERONCINO, AND MORE

1325
00:50:45,242 --> 00:50:48,412
Up against him is Chef Ho-young.
What are you making?

1326
00:50:48,478 --> 00:50:52,049
THE RESPONSE TO HIS DANCE
WILL AFFECT THE RESULT!

1327
00:50:52,115 --> 00:50:53,583
The name of my dish is…

1328
00:50:53,650 --> 00:50:55,318
The name of my dish is…

1329
00:50:55,385 --> 00:50:58,288
I'm going to make seafood stew.

1330
00:50:58,355 --> 00:51:01,391
And with that, I'll serve fish balls

1331
00:51:01,458 --> 00:51:03,560
made with the soybean pulp

1332
00:51:03,627 --> 00:51:06,897
your wife left after making tofu.

1333
00:51:06,963 --> 00:51:09,299
But if she doesn't make tofu,

1334
00:51:10,067 --> 00:51:11,268
we won't have soybean pulp.

1335
00:51:11,334 --> 00:51:13,070
A DISH SHE CAN'T MAKE
WITHOUT SOYBEAN PULP?

1336
00:51:13,670 --> 00:51:15,705
I also saw bigfin reef squid,

1337
00:51:15,772 --> 00:51:18,875
so I'll broil it on a gridiron

1338
00:51:18,942 --> 00:51:20,577
for you to enjoy with soju.

1339
00:51:20,644 --> 00:51:22,679
They're basically bar snacks for soju.

1340
00:51:22,746 --> 00:51:24,047
-That sounds amazing.
-For soju.

1341
00:51:24,114 --> 00:51:25,782
-Are you two ready?
-Yes.

1342
00:51:25,849 --> 00:51:29,119
All right, then.
Let us begin your cook-off.

1343
00:51:29,186 --> 00:51:31,621
This is the last match
of the regular season.

1344
00:51:31,688 --> 00:51:34,458
This man never loses
when it comes to seafood.

1345
00:51:34,524 --> 00:51:37,594
Chef Jung Ho-young,
aka the seafood sniper.

1346
00:51:37,661 --> 00:51:39,896
<i>But this man never loses against Ho-young.</i>

1347
00:51:39,963 --> 00:51:43,767
Chef Son Jong-won,
aka Jung Ho-young sniper.

1348
00:51:43,834 --> 00:51:46,369
Which one of the two
will move up in ranking

1349
00:51:46,436 --> 00:51:49,706
to second place?

1350
00:51:49,773 --> 00:51:52,409
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1351
00:51:52,476 --> 00:51:53,643
Let's go!

1352
00:51:54,211 --> 00:51:55,245
WIN AND BECOME 2ND PLACE!

1353
00:51:55,312 --> 00:51:56,546
OR LOSE AND FALL TO 5TH PLACE!

1354
00:51:56,613 --> 00:51:59,583
The last round of the regular league.

1355
00:51:59,649 --> 00:52:02,452
HO-YOUNG BEGINS BY COOKING MUSSELS

1356
00:52:02,953 --> 00:52:04,387
-He's using mussels.
-Mussels.

1357
00:52:04,454 --> 00:52:06,189
Shin-soo said he loves mussels earlier.

1358
00:52:06,756 --> 00:52:08,125
MUSSELS

1359
00:52:08,191 --> 00:52:11,728
He's already got this in the bag.

1360
00:52:11,795 --> 00:52:13,230
SCALLOPS

1361
00:52:13,296 --> 00:52:16,133
He's using soybean pulp and an egg.

1362
00:52:16,199 --> 00:52:19,736
-He's mixing soybean pulp and an egg?
-And starch.

1363
00:52:19,803 --> 00:52:22,072
Is he grinding that to make fish balls?

1364
00:52:22,939 --> 00:52:24,674
But Shin-soo asked just before the round

1365
00:52:24,741 --> 00:52:26,409
what they should do
if they're out of soybean pulp

1366
00:52:26,476 --> 00:52:27,944
on days she doesn't make tofu.

1367
00:52:29,112 --> 00:52:30,413
What now?

1368
00:52:32,582 --> 00:52:33,483
SMILE FIRST

1369
00:52:33,550 --> 00:52:34,384
What did he say?

1370
00:52:34,451 --> 00:52:35,919
-What?
-What?

1371
00:52:35,986 --> 00:52:38,588
That you won't have soybean pulp
on days she doesn't make tofu.

1372
00:52:38,655 --> 00:52:41,591
She always makes tofu for him
because he loves it so much.

1373
00:52:41,658 --> 00:52:43,994
When she doesn't have it,
she can use tofu, right?

1374
00:52:44,060 --> 00:52:45,762
-Yes, she can use tofu.
-Right?

1375
00:52:45,829 --> 00:52:46,796
AND

1376
00:52:46,863 --> 00:52:48,632
-Small octopus?
-Small octopus.

1377
00:52:48,698 --> 00:52:50,600
-Squid legs.
-Squid legs?

1378
00:52:50,667 --> 00:52:52,435
-Bigfin reef squid.
-Squid legs.

1379
00:52:52,502 --> 00:52:55,105
-It's squid.
-The bigfin reef squid.

1380
00:52:55,172 --> 00:52:57,607
He's using smoked salmon.

1381
00:52:57,674 --> 00:52:59,276
-I see.
-Smoked salmon.

1382
00:52:59,342 --> 00:53:02,045
Does smoked salmon taste okay
when it's grilled?

1383
00:53:02,112 --> 00:53:04,681
-I'm making carpaccio with this.
-Carpaccio.

1384
00:53:04,748 --> 00:53:06,082
Is he making carpaccio?

1385
00:53:06,149 --> 00:53:07,717
He's making salmon carpaccio.

1386
00:53:08,318 --> 00:53:09,619
He's making two different dishes.

1387
00:53:09,686 --> 00:53:10,987
FLATTENING

1388
00:53:11,054 --> 00:53:13,690
1. LAYER SMOKED SALMON PIECES
AND FLATTEN WITH A ROLLING PIN

1389
00:53:14,191 --> 00:53:15,525
NEXT, A SQUARE MOLD!

1390
00:53:15,592 --> 00:53:18,195
He's making it pretty with a mold.

1391
00:53:18,261 --> 00:53:20,297
He layered them
and cut them into a square.

1392
00:53:20,363 --> 00:53:23,133
Are those chives?
He's chopping the chives.

1393
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:24,634
He's chopping them like that?

1394
00:53:24,701 --> 00:53:25,535
That's so delicate.

1395
00:53:25,602 --> 00:53:27,237
SMALLER PIECES INCREASE THE SMELL

1396
00:53:27,304 --> 00:53:28,905
ASTONISHED

1397
00:53:28,972 --> 00:53:30,607
Capers and onion.

1398
00:53:30,674 --> 00:53:31,708
ONION

1399
00:53:31,775 --> 00:53:33,109
-Capers.
-Yes, capers.

1400
00:53:35,145 --> 00:53:37,013
CHOPPING LIKE A GRINDER!

1401
00:53:37,080 --> 00:53:38,381
He makes cuts on the squid.

1402
00:53:38,448 --> 00:53:40,016
I'M GOOD WITH A KNIFE TOO!

1403
00:53:40,083 --> 00:53:41,718
He begins to score the squid.

1404
00:53:41,785 --> 00:53:43,787
This is his specialty.

1405
00:53:43,853 --> 00:53:46,022
Yes, Ho-young is doing a great job.

1406
00:53:46,089 --> 00:53:47,924
HO-YOUNG THE SCORING MACHINE!

1407
00:53:47,991 --> 00:53:49,793
My gosh.

1408
00:53:49,859 --> 00:53:51,695
No one wants to take fifth place.

1409
00:53:51,761 --> 00:53:54,798
Second place and fifth place
are worlds apart.

1410
00:53:56,299 --> 00:53:58,468
THERE IT IS! HIS BEST MOVE!

1411
00:53:58,535 --> 00:54:00,003
DANCING KNIFE ON THE BOARD

1412
00:54:00,070 --> 00:54:02,973
And Jong-won fights back by cutting too.

1413
00:54:03,540 --> 00:54:05,775
Chef Nam-no
gave me this knife as a present.

1414
00:54:05,842 --> 00:54:07,644
Yes, I gave it to him.

1415
00:54:07,711 --> 00:54:08,612
JEEZ…

1416
00:54:08,678 --> 00:54:09,646
As a present?

1417
00:54:10,380 --> 00:54:11,715
-Sorry?
-As a present?

1418
00:54:11,781 --> 00:54:12,949
What about me?

1419
00:54:13,016 --> 00:54:13,917
What about me?

1420
00:54:13,984 --> 00:54:15,085
You're awful.

1421
00:54:15,151 --> 00:54:16,586
He's now siding with Jong-won.

1422
00:54:16,653 --> 00:54:17,854
-He had a reason.
-Yes.

1423
00:54:17,921 --> 00:54:19,322
He has a soft spot for good looks.

1424
00:54:19,389 --> 00:54:20,223
That's true.

1425
00:54:20,757 --> 00:54:24,494
Chopped onion and capers,
perfect matches with smoked salmon.

1426
00:54:24,561 --> 00:54:25,662
AND LEMON!

1427
00:54:25,729 --> 00:54:26,596
LEMON ZEST

1428
00:54:26,663 --> 00:54:28,098
3. TOP WITH LEMON ZEST,
AVOCADO OIL, HORSERADISH

1429
00:54:28,164 --> 00:54:30,533
It's mostly used with chives,

1430
00:54:30,600 --> 00:54:31,568
so he added those too.

1431
00:54:31,635 --> 00:54:32,936
That adds a nice smell.

1432
00:54:34,337 --> 00:54:37,574
Huh? He's about to broil it.
What's that thing called again?

1433
00:54:37,641 --> 00:54:39,676
He'll skewer that
and broil it over a gridiron.

1434
00:54:39,743 --> 00:54:41,544
-Are you grilling it for the stew?
-No.

1435
00:54:41,611 --> 00:54:44,080
-It's a side dish.
-On the side.

1436
00:54:44,147 --> 00:54:45,682
Bigfin reef squid is huge.

1437
00:54:45,749 --> 00:54:48,852
It's usually tough to skewer a squid.

1438
00:54:48,918 --> 00:54:51,454
It looks like a kite.

1439
00:54:51,521 --> 00:54:54,658
3. PARBOIL CUT BIGFIN REEF SQUID
IN SEAFOOD BROTH

1440
00:54:55,225 --> 00:54:57,727
QUICKLY PARBOILED

1441
00:54:57,794 --> 00:55:01,464
