Their styles are so different.

1686
01:03:33,342 --> 01:03:39,782
We have the seafood bar snacks
made just for Shin-soo.

1687
01:03:39,849 --> 01:03:43,419
-They look beautiful.
-They do, don't they?

1688
01:03:43,486 --> 01:03:46,289
Please try Chef Jong-won's RomantisChoo.

1689
01:03:46,856 --> 01:03:49,091
DELICATELY STACKED
AVOCADO SALMON CARPACCIO

1690
01:03:50,326 --> 01:03:52,562
AND TENDER SALMON STEAK

1691
01:03:53,596 --> 01:03:56,532
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S ROMANTISCHOO

1692
01:03:57,466 --> 01:04:00,102
He made two dishes

1693
01:04:00,169 --> 01:04:02,238
-his wife would love a lot.
-Yes.

1694
01:04:02,305 --> 01:04:04,040
Please try it with the wine we prepared.

1695
01:04:04,106 --> 01:04:06,008
-We prepared wine, didn't we?
-Yes.

1696
01:04:06,075 --> 01:04:06,976
Server!

1697
01:04:08,377 --> 01:04:09,679
There it is.

1698
01:04:09,745 --> 01:04:11,113
WHITE WINE TO GO WITH THE DISHES

1699
01:04:11,180 --> 01:04:12,215
Just like that.

1700
01:04:12,281 --> 01:04:16,586
I remembered how you said
you two were in your second honeymoon,

1701
01:04:16,652 --> 01:04:20,823
so I made those so that you two would
have a romantic night over wine.

1702
01:04:20,890 --> 01:04:22,558
It goes so perfectly together.

1703
01:04:22,625 --> 01:04:24,327
THE FIRST SIP OF WINE

1704
01:04:24,393 --> 01:04:25,761
A sip of white wine.

1705
01:04:25,828 --> 01:04:27,663
-White wine.
-Yes.

1706
01:04:27,730 --> 01:04:28,598
How should he begin?

1707
01:04:28,664 --> 01:04:32,134
-Try the smoked salmon and avocado first.
-The smoked salmon.

1708
01:04:33,069 --> 01:04:35,638
-He served it so beautifully.
-It's so pretty.

1709
01:04:35,705 --> 01:04:37,974
We saw him stack those together.

1710
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:45,047
The seafood bar snack.

1711
01:04:45,114 --> 01:04:47,250
Smoked salmon and avocado.

1712
01:04:47,316 --> 01:04:50,086
Shin-soo begins to smile a little.

1713
01:04:51,821 --> 01:04:53,990
-It's so good.
-I see.

1714
01:04:54,056 --> 01:04:55,391
Is it that good?

1715
01:04:55,458 --> 01:04:57,593
It's just smoked salmon with avocado,

1716
01:04:57,660 --> 01:05:01,264
but it tastes like a dish
I would eat at a fine dining restaurant.

1717
01:05:01,330 --> 01:05:04,033
What's the sauce on the side?

1718
01:05:04,100 --> 01:05:08,037
It's a mix of lemon juice and avocado oil.
I saw that you had some.

1719
01:05:08,604 --> 01:05:11,741
When we eat avocados,
we rarely use the same oil.

1720
01:05:11,807 --> 01:05:14,877
But he added avocado oil over the top.

1721
01:05:14,944 --> 01:05:17,179
-It comes with salmon, though.
-Yes.

1722
01:05:17,246 --> 01:05:18,881
Give him some more.

1723
01:05:18,948 --> 01:05:21,417
-He's eating a lot.
-Things are looking great.

1724
01:05:22,184 --> 01:05:24,120
CHEWING CAREFULLY AND SAVORING

1725
01:05:24,186 --> 01:05:25,154
So?

1726
01:05:25,721 --> 01:05:27,757
-It's so good.
-It is?

1727
01:05:29,225 --> 01:05:30,159
INHALES SHARPLY

1728
01:05:30,226 --> 01:05:32,528
It's a shame
that I have to eat this alone.

1729
01:05:32,595 --> 01:05:33,729
I'm sure.

1730
01:05:33,796 --> 01:05:35,298
-His wife.
-You have to share it with her.

1731
01:05:35,364 --> 01:05:37,166
I can come over and make it for you.

1732
01:05:37,733 --> 01:05:39,068
MAKING HIS CASE TO GET 2ND PLACE

1733
01:05:39,936 --> 01:05:41,537
He keeps making his case.

1734
01:05:41,604 --> 01:05:43,205
One becomes second place,
the other, fifth.

1735
01:05:43,272 --> 01:05:44,807
Don't be so sad.

1736
01:05:44,874 --> 01:05:47,810
I can shoot for another ten hours now.

1737
01:05:47,877 --> 01:05:49,545
Ten hours?

1738
01:05:49,612 --> 01:05:51,580
I'm sorry, but we have to go home.

1739
01:05:51,647 --> 01:05:54,283
REFUSES TO WORK OVERTIME

1740
01:05:54,350 --> 01:05:56,552
Next, the salmon steak.

1741
01:05:56,619 --> 01:05:58,788
-I wonder what it's like.
-What's the salmon steak like?

1742
01:05:59,355 --> 01:06:00,256
DABBED IN SAUCE

1743
01:06:00,323 --> 01:06:02,024
It's cooked perfectly.

1744
01:06:02,091 --> 01:06:02,959
It looks so good.

1745
01:06:05,227 --> 01:06:06,595
HE SMILES YET AGAIN

1746
01:06:06,662 --> 01:06:08,631
Another smile.

1747
01:06:08,698 --> 01:06:10,633
CURIOUS

1748
01:06:10,700 --> 01:06:14,770
I've had many salmon steaks in my life,

1749
01:06:14,837 --> 01:06:17,640
but this one is
on a completely different level.

1750
01:06:17,707 --> 01:06:20,009
I've only had them back in America.

1751
01:06:20,943 --> 01:06:24,547
This one has a touch of Asian flavor.

1752
01:06:24,613 --> 01:06:28,617
<i>It has a hint of sweetness</i>
<i>like teriyaki sauce,</i>

1753
01:06:28,684 --> 01:06:31,220
so it doesn't taste
anything like the flavor I dislike.

1754
01:06:31,287 --> 01:06:35,124
If I closed my eyes and ate it,
I wouldn't have known it was salmon.

1755
01:06:35,191 --> 01:06:36,659
This is something

1756
01:06:36,726 --> 01:06:39,695
-I can eat every single day.
-You can eat it every day?

1757
01:06:40,196 --> 01:06:41,764
Good one, Jong-won!

1758
01:06:41,831 --> 01:06:43,299
JONG-WON TAKES THE LEAD

1759
01:06:43,366 --> 01:06:44,834
All right!

1760
01:06:45,401 --> 01:06:46,869
SIPS WINE FIRST FOR THE CHASER

1761
01:06:46,936 --> 01:06:48,838
-It looks so good.
-He looks so cool.

1762
01:06:48,904 --> 01:06:52,274
He shares
great compliments for the dishes.

1763
01:06:52,341 --> 01:06:54,944
It was made
with lots of butter and vegetables.

1764
01:06:55,511 --> 01:06:57,780
A sip of wine, and then the food.

1765
01:06:58,881 --> 01:07:00,483
-Gosh.
-"Gosh."

1766
01:07:00,549 --> 01:07:01,784
Does it go well with wine?

1767
01:07:01,851 --> 01:07:04,653
-It's a fantastic combination.
-Is it?

1768
01:07:04,720 --> 01:07:06,122
HAPPY, SAD

1769
01:07:06,188 --> 01:07:07,523
My wife would love this.

1770
01:07:07,590 --> 01:07:08,891
EVEN HIS WIFE WOULD LOVE IT

1771
01:07:08,958 --> 01:07:11,360
-His wife would love it.
-She would.

1772
01:07:11,427 --> 01:07:13,262
-It was on a different level?
-It was.

1773
01:07:13,329 --> 01:07:15,931
Ho-young looks anxious,
thinking the stew may boil down.

1774
01:07:16,565 --> 01:07:17,867
-Really?
-You should try that.

1775
01:07:17,933 --> 01:07:20,269
-This one first, then.
-We can't let it boil down.

1776
01:07:20,836 --> 01:07:23,339
SEAFOOD SOUP WITH VARIOUS SEAFOOD
AND FISH BALLS MADE FROM SCRATCH

1777
01:07:24,707 --> 01:07:27,276
SERVED WITH A SIDE
OF CAREFULLY BROILED BIGFIN REEF SQUID

1778
01:07:28,344 --> 01:07:31,347
CHEF JUNG HO-YOUNG'S
MR. CHOO, SHOT OF SOJU, CHOO

1779
01:07:31,414 --> 01:07:34,683
The atmosphere changes completely
with these two dishes here.

1780
01:07:34,750 --> 01:07:37,720
-We're now in Japan.
-It's like a bar in Japan.

1781
01:07:37,787 --> 01:07:40,856
-That means he should drink something new.
-Something new.

1782
01:07:40,923 --> 01:07:43,492
-Soju.
-He must drink soju now.

1783
01:07:43,559 --> 01:07:46,028
Lose the wine and go with soju.

1784
01:07:46,095 --> 01:07:47,363
The server is doing a great job.

1785
01:07:47,430 --> 01:07:48,964
THIS TIME, SOJU

1786
01:07:49,031 --> 01:07:50,599
-Gosh.
-What should he eat first?

1787
01:07:50,666 --> 01:07:55,171
You'll see both the fish balls
and scallops on the bottom,

1788
01:07:55,237 --> 01:07:57,640
so try those with the broth.

1789
01:07:58,207 --> 01:08:00,643
PLUMP FISH BALLS

1790
01:08:00,709 --> 01:08:02,111
Isn't that too big?

1791
01:08:02,178 --> 01:08:03,012
He can cut it in half.

1792
01:08:03,579 --> 01:08:04,513
WELCOMING FOOD WITH SOJU

1793
01:08:04,580 --> 01:08:06,382
-A drink of soju.
-This will be perfect.

1794
01:08:06,949 --> 01:08:08,317
DRINKING WITH HIS EYES

1795
01:08:08,384 --> 01:08:11,187
-He has almost lost it.
-Yes, it's driving me crazy.

1796
01:08:13,889 --> 01:08:15,324
My gosh. Look at him.

1797
01:08:16,091 --> 01:08:17,226
My gosh!

1798
01:08:17,293 --> 01:08:19,228
This is driving me crazy!

1799
01:08:19,295 --> 01:08:21,197
ABOUT TO FAINT
BECAUSE HE WANTS TO TRY IT SO MUCH

1800
01:08:21,263 --> 01:08:22,498
He has to try the squid too.

1801
01:08:23,532 --> 01:08:24,900
HAND ON FOREHEAD

1802
01:08:25,868 --> 01:08:27,503
It must be crazy good.

1803
01:08:27,570 --> 01:08:29,205
I'm craving soju too.

1804
01:08:29,271 --> 01:08:31,440
-You don't drink.
-Although I don't drink.

1805
01:08:31,507 --> 01:08:32,541
Chef Sung-jun doesn't drink.

1806
01:08:32,608 --> 01:08:34,477
So? Does it go well with soju?

1807
01:08:35,044 --> 01:08:37,146
I don't even have to say it.

1808
01:08:37,213 --> 01:08:38,914
I made those fish balls

1809
01:08:38,981 --> 01:08:41,417
<i>with the soybean pulp that</i>
<i>your wife left behind after making tofu.</i>

1810
01:08:41,484 --> 01:08:43,452
-Really?
-He made them with soybean pulp.

1811
01:08:43,519 --> 01:08:44,920
HE NEVER EVEN IMAGINED

1812
01:08:44,987 --> 01:08:48,424
-I noticed after you said it.
-Yes, he mentioned that earlier.

1813
01:08:48,491 --> 01:08:49,825
You can taste the nutty flavor.

1814
01:08:49,892 --> 01:08:51,393
CHASING FIERCELY

1815
01:08:51,460 --> 01:08:55,664
He uses the soybean pulp his wife left
after making him tofu from scratch.

1816
01:08:56,832 --> 01:08:58,567
CAREFULLY REQUESTING SOJU

1817
01:09:00,336 --> 01:09:01,537
WETS HIS MOUTH

1818
01:09:02,104 --> 01:09:03,639
COMPLETELY ABSORBED

1819
01:09:03,706 --> 01:09:05,774
-Are you serious?
-This is nice.

1820
01:09:05,841 --> 01:09:07,209
He needed that soju.

1821
01:09:07,276 --> 01:09:08,944
Gosh, it looks so good.

1822
01:09:09,512 --> 01:09:11,447
Please try the squid too.

1823
01:09:11,514 --> 01:09:12,948
It smelled amazing.

1824
01:09:13,015 --> 01:09:15,618
-The squid.
-Are you trying the squid?

1825
01:09:15,684 --> 01:09:18,387
It looks really juicy with the sauce.

1826
01:09:18,454 --> 01:09:19,822
YUM

1827
01:09:19,889 --> 01:09:20,990
It came with sauce.

1828
01:09:21,657 --> 01:09:23,292
AN AUTOMATIC SMILE

1829
01:09:24,326 --> 01:09:26,228
HE SUDDENLY CLEANS THE TABLE?

1830
01:09:26,729 --> 01:09:28,597
-It would make you faint.
-It must be so good.

1831
01:09:28,664 --> 01:09:29,798
He planned everything.

1832
01:09:29,865 --> 01:09:31,200
NECK-AND-NECK BATTLE

1833
01:09:31,267 --> 01:09:33,435
The soju must go so well with those.

1834
01:09:33,502 --> 01:09:35,504
I'm not sure if it is
because this is bigfin reef squid

1835
01:09:35,571 --> 01:09:38,307
or if it is the way he broiled the squid.

1836
01:09:38,374 --> 01:09:40,142
But it's really chewy.

1837
01:09:40,910 --> 01:09:42,811
It must be because it's bigfin reef squid.

1838
01:09:42,878 --> 01:09:44,947
It's not too sweet, either.

1839
01:09:45,014 --> 01:09:47,183
It's so savory in my mouth.

1840
01:09:47,249 --> 01:09:49,885
-I see.
-It must be that good.

1841
01:09:49,952 --> 01:09:51,787
Hyun-jin looks troubled.

1842
01:09:51,854 --> 01:09:54,890
-He's okay so far.
-Hyun-jin looks stressed out.

1843
01:09:54,957 --> 01:09:56,258
Let's give him time to think.

1844
01:09:56,325 --> 01:09:59,461
-Let's give him some time to decide.
-And some time for Hyun-jin to eat.

1845
01:09:59,528 --> 01:10:02,097
It's an honor to have
such world-renowned sports stars here.

1846
01:10:02,164 --> 01:10:03,165
PLEASED

1847
01:10:03,232 --> 01:10:04,300
White wine.

1848
01:10:04,366 --> 01:10:05,601
I thought you'd have a lot.

1849
01:10:09,939 --> 01:10:11,974
He wets his mouth first.

1850
01:10:12,775 --> 01:10:14,710
This is driving me crazy.

1851
01:10:14,777 --> 01:10:16,579
-It's everything I like.
-It must be so tender.

1852
01:10:17,513 --> 01:10:18,914
It melts in his mouth.

1853
01:10:19,481 --> 01:10:20,382
IT DOES

1854
01:10:20,449 --> 01:10:21,584
-It does, right?
-It does.

1855
01:10:21,650 --> 01:10:22,851
-It must.
-Does it?

1856
01:10:22,918 --> 01:10:26,488
-Yes.
-We had salmon back in America, right?

1857
01:10:26,555 --> 01:10:29,058
You get grilled salmon
at the ballpark, right?

1858
01:10:29,124 --> 01:10:34,063
Yes, and it's literally just grilled
without any sauce

1859
01:10:34,129 --> 01:10:35,931
but with some veggies on the side.

1860
01:10:35,998 --> 01:10:39,268
-It's dry, isn't it?
-Yes, it's dry.

1861
01:10:39,335 --> 01:10:42,771
<i>It's much juicier and tenderer</i>
<i>with this sauce.</i>

1862
01:10:43,672 --> 01:10:44,707
ANOTHER BITE OF THE SALMON

1863
01:10:44,773 --> 01:10:45,841
And it's not too salty?

1864
01:10:45,908 --> 01:10:47,276
-It's not.
-No?

1865
01:10:48,444 --> 01:10:51,347
Gosh, this is hard to watch.

1866
01:10:51,413 --> 01:10:52,982
Next, some soju.

1867
01:10:53,048 --> 01:10:54,383
-Thank you.
-Sure.

1868
01:10:57,086 --> 01:10:58,287
CHUGS

1869
01:10:58,354 --> 01:10:59,822
He deleted that.

1870
01:10:59,888 --> 01:11:01,624
Let me pour another one just in case.

1871
01:11:01,690 --> 01:11:02,992
A REFILL

1872
01:11:03,058 --> 01:11:05,361
He has to move back and forth.

1873
01:11:05,427 --> 01:11:06,495
I'm tired too.

1874
01:11:06,562 --> 01:11:08,697
He'll go back to the drink
after a bite of the snack.

1875
01:11:08,764 --> 01:11:11,066
Try the seafood and the fish balls.

1876
01:11:11,133 --> 01:11:12,101
THE FISH BALL AND STEW

1877
01:11:14,603 --> 01:11:19,141
It's amazing to know
he made the fish balls with soybean pulp.

1878
01:11:19,208 --> 01:11:20,075
-The fish balls.
-Yes.

1879
01:11:20,142 --> 01:11:23,779
The combination of soju
and this stew is perfect for my taste.

1880
01:11:23,846 --> 01:11:24,780
TOTALLY HYUN-JIN'S TASTE

1881
01:11:24,847 --> 01:11:25,914
-Is it your taste?
-Yes.

1882
01:11:25,981 --> 01:11:27,883
-I see.
-Try the squid.

1883
01:11:27,950 --> 01:11:29,451
Will you try the squid?

1884
01:11:29,518 --> 01:11:31,720
Yes, another sip of soju.

1885
01:11:31,787 --> 01:11:32,888
The squid.

1886
01:11:33,922 --> 01:11:35,291
The bigfin reef squid.

1887
01:11:36,558 --> 01:11:38,327
It may have gone cold by now.

1888
01:11:41,230 --> 01:11:43,198
LAUGHING

1889
01:11:43,265 --> 01:11:44,233
DID THEY JUST COMMUNICATE?

1890
01:11:44,300 --> 01:11:45,501
The eyes.

1891
01:11:45,567 --> 01:11:48,203
-They communicated with their eyes.
-Yes, they exchanged glances.

1892
01:11:48,270 --> 01:11:49,972
I wonder what that was about.

1893
01:11:50,539 --> 01:11:51,807
It's perfect for my taste.

1894
01:11:53,542 --> 01:11:55,678
It's very tender,

1895
01:11:55,744 --> 01:11:57,980
yet it has a smoky taste
because he broiled it.

1896
01:11:58,047 --> 01:12:01,216
If Shin-soo and I drink soju over this,

1897
01:12:01,283 --> 01:12:03,285
we can probably drink all night.

1898
01:12:04,987 --> 01:12:07,389
This is so hard for me.

1899
01:12:07,456 --> 01:12:09,825
-Is it?
-This is so hard.

1900
01:12:09,892 --> 01:12:10,893
That sounds like trouble.

1901
01:12:10,959 --> 01:12:12,895
I thought nothing would

1902
01:12:12,961 --> 01:12:14,663
make my life hard once I retired.

1903
01:12:15,230 --> 01:12:17,099
A DECISION AS TOUGH AS HIS CAREER(?)

1904
01:12:17,166 --> 01:12:19,234
-The entire nation is watching.
-The hardest.

1905
01:12:19,301 --> 01:12:20,602
And even from abroad.

1906
01:12:20,669 --> 01:12:25,507
Shin-soo is about to make
the last decision of the regular league.

1907
01:12:25,574 --> 01:12:26,842
Also, according to this result,

1908
01:12:26,909 --> 01:12:29,611
the two chefs' fate will be decided.

1909
01:12:29,678 --> 01:12:32,081
<i>Press one for Son Jong-won.</i>

1910
01:12:32,147 --> 01:12:34,350
<i>Press two for Jung Ho-young.</i>

1911
01:12:34,416 --> 01:12:35,918
Make your decision

1912
01:12:35,984 --> 01:12:38,620
-and press the button!
-Oh, dang it.

1913
01:12:39,188 --> 01:12:41,390
What do you mean, "Oh, dang it"?

1914
01:12:41,457 --> 01:12:44,793
-It's that tough to decide.
-It must be.

1915
01:12:44,860 --> 01:12:46,662
-I chose one.
-You did?

1916
01:12:46,729 --> 01:12:47,696
He pressed it.

1917
01:12:47,763 --> 01:12:48,931
The die has been cast.

1918
01:12:48,997 --> 01:12:53,769
Which one of the two
has captured Shin-soo's heart?

1919
01:12:53,836 --> 01:12:56,839
The final match of the regular league.

1920
01:12:56,905 --> 01:12:58,874
Let's find out who won!

1921
01:13:00,008 --> 01:13:01,944
Seafood Bar Snack, Want Choo.

1922
01:13:02,010 --> 01:13:05,614
-You can't watch it, can you?
-I can't. I'm so nervous.

1923
01:13:05,681 --> 01:13:09,752
-I really can't watch this.
-Who'll make the playoffs as second place?

1924
01:13:09,818 --> 01:13:11,253
Will it be Jung Ho-young

1925
01:13:11,320 --> 01:13:13,021
or Son Jong-won?

1926
01:13:13,088 --> 01:13:15,691
They both have nine wins so far!

1927
01:13:15,758 --> 01:13:17,893
Who won?

1928
01:13:17,960 --> 01:13:20,095
-Oh, no.
-Who won this round?

1929
01:13:20,162 --> 01:13:22,464
-Who is it?
-Who's in second place?

1930
01:13:22,531 --> 01:13:23,465
Who is it?

1931
01:13:23,532 --> 01:13:25,033
JUNG HO-YOUNG

1932
01:13:25,100 --> 01:13:26,068
Jung Ho-young wins!

1933
01:13:26,135 --> 01:13:28,670
JUNG HO-YOUNG'S
MR. CHOO, SHOT OF SOJU, CHOO

1934
01:13:28,737 --> 01:13:30,372
THE LAST ROUND OF THE REGULAR LEAGUE

1935
01:13:30,439 --> 01:13:32,408
Ho-young comes in second place!

1936
01:13:32,474 --> 01:13:34,777
He's the winner!

1937
01:13:34,843 --> 01:13:36,378
CONGRATULATIONS

1938
01:13:36,445 --> 01:13:38,814
That was such a neck-and-neck match.

1939
01:13:38,881 --> 01:13:41,283
I thought it'd be the salmon.

1940
01:13:41,350 --> 01:13:43,218
-I see.
-He would've thought of his wife.

1941
01:13:43,285 --> 01:13:45,421
As for the salmon dishes,

1942
01:13:45,487 --> 01:13:47,623
it felt like we should dress up

1943
01:13:47,689 --> 01:13:50,058
and go to a nice restaurant to eat that.

1944
01:13:50,125 --> 01:13:54,163
-But we're having this at home, right?
-At home.

1945
01:13:54,229 --> 01:13:56,765
-That was why I made the decision.
-I see.

1946
01:13:56,832 --> 01:14:00,035
He had to make such a tough decision.

1947
01:14:00,102 --> 01:14:01,403
In this case,

1948
01:14:01,470 --> 01:14:05,007
<i>Ho-young now has ten wins, seven losses.</i>

1949
01:14:05,073 --> 01:14:09,478
<i>Chef Jong-won is in fifth place,</i>
<i>and Chef Ho-young is in second place.</i>

1950
01:14:09,545 --> 01:14:12,381
<i>He'll make it to the playoffs</i>
<i>in second place.</i>

1951
01:14:12,448 --> 01:14:13,615
<i>Congratulations.</i>

1952
01:14:13,682 --> 01:14:14,983
2025 CHAMPIONSHIP PLAYOFF MATCHUPS

1953
01:14:15,050 --> 01:14:16,785
<i>The decision has been made.</i>

1954
01:14:16,852 --> 01:14:18,987
You'll have to play the first round.

1955
01:14:19,054 --> 01:14:21,757
Well, as a chef, it's a good thing
that I get to cook a lot.

1956
01:14:21,824 --> 01:14:23,592
I'll think of this as a great opportunity.

1957
01:14:23,659 --> 01:14:25,961
-I see.
-He's so eloquent too.

1958
01:14:26,028 --> 01:14:27,629
-How cool.
-He's so genuine.

1959
01:14:27,696 --> 01:14:30,232
But we don't know for sure
if you'll get to cook a lot.

1960
01:14:31,700 --> 01:14:32,701
That's true.

1961
01:14:32,768 --> 01:14:35,037
-We'll have to see.
-Don't say it like that.

1962
01:14:35,103 --> 01:14:36,472
You're way too extreme.

1963
01:14:36,538 --> 01:14:37,973
-You'll have to do well.
-You must win.

1964
01:14:38,040 --> 01:14:39,541
HE WANTS HIM TO DO WELL AND COOK A LOT

1965
01:14:39,608 --> 01:14:43,979
We'll come back next week
with the championship.

1966
01:14:44,046 --> 01:14:46,048
Thank you. Please put a star on him!

1967
01:14:46,114 --> 01:14:46,949
MOVING UP AS 2ND PLACE

1968
01:14:47,015 --> 01:14:48,917
Please put it on, Shin-soo.

1969
01:14:48,984 --> 01:14:51,820
Chef Ho-young makes the playoffs
in second place.

1970
01:14:51,887 --> 01:14:52,721
Congratulations!

1971
01:14:52,788 --> 01:14:54,056
Congrats!

1972
01:14:54,122 --> 01:14:55,257
He's second place.

1973
01:14:55,324 --> 01:14:56,358
CONGRA-CHOO-LATIONS

1974
01:14:56,758 --> 01:14:58,660
It's finally the playoff,

1975
01:14:58,727 --> 01:15:00,295
the 2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Championship.

1976
01:15:00,362 --> 01:15:01,663
ONE TROPHY ONLY FOR THE WINNER

1977
01:15:02,531 --> 01:15:03,398
I want that.

1978
01:15:03,465 --> 01:15:04,500
The variety show champions,

1979
01:15:04,566 --> 01:15:06,535
please welcome Kim Won-hun and Lee Su-ji!

1980
01:15:06,602 --> 01:15:07,536
Are you thinking back on it?

1981
01:15:07,603 --> 01:15:08,670
I'm at <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

1982
01:15:08,737 --> 01:15:10,506
I'm a much better cook!

1983
01:15:11,640 --> 01:15:13,775
CRYING FROM LAUGHING TOO MUCH

1984
01:15:13,842 --> 01:15:16,545
Every single restaurant recommendation
Won-hun made was a success.

1985
01:15:16,612 --> 01:15:17,613
He knows what's good.

1986
01:15:17,679 --> 01:15:19,114
She finds everything delicious.

1987
01:15:19,181 --> 01:15:21,350
She had lots of hand cream on her hands.

1988
01:15:21,416 --> 01:15:22,651
It smelled like <i>jokbal</i>, pig's feet.

1989
01:15:22,718 --> 01:15:24,553
THEY KNOW WHAT'S DELICIOUS

1990
01:15:24,620 --> 01:15:25,954
<i>The </i>Chef & My Fridge<i> Championship.</i>

1991
01:15:26,021 --> 01:15:28,390
Jong-won never makes anything
half-heartedly.

1992
01:15:28,457 --> 01:15:30,993
-That's how he's doing it.
-Look at that detail.

1993
01:15:31,059 --> 01:15:32,861
Like a moth to a flame,
she's never afraid.

1994
01:15:32,928 --> 01:15:34,129
It's my personal hot pot rice.

1995
01:15:34,196 --> 01:15:35,130
It tastes amazing.

1996
01:15:35,197 --> 01:15:36,331
EUN-YEONG, ON A FEISTY ROLL

1997
01:15:36,398 --> 01:15:37,633
I will win this fair and square

1998
01:15:37,699 --> 01:15:38,834
with my skills.

1999
01:15:38,901 --> 01:15:40,102
DEEP-FRYING, I CAN DO

2000
01:15:40,168 --> 01:15:42,271
This one looks too burnt.

2001
01:15:42,337 --> 01:15:43,171
IS THIS RIGHT?

2002
01:15:43,238 --> 01:15:44,239
It looks like asphalt.

2003
01:15:44,306 --> 01:15:46,074
-He's obsessing over it.
-Lose it.

2004
01:15:46,141 --> 01:15:47,409
Will Won-hun like it?

2005
01:15:47,476 --> 01:15:48,644
It must be really good.

2006
01:15:48,710 --> 01:15:50,579
I kind of want this as my last meal.

2007
01:15:50,646 --> 01:15:53,115
The one who receives the star
will move on to the next round!

2008
01:15:53,181 --> 01:15:54,349
EVERYONE IS IN SHOCK

2009
01:15:54,416 --> 01:15:56,218
WHEN THEY FIND OUT THE RESULT

2010
01:15:56,285 --> 01:15:57,286
<i>That was a huge twist.</i>

2011
01:15:57,352 --> 01:15:58,353
<i>It doesn't make any sense.</i>

2012
01:15:59,688 --> 01:16:01,890
-I'm sorry. Are you here to watch TV?
-It's a lot of fun.

2013
01:16:01,957 --> 01:16:04,159
-Is it?
-This is why the show lasted a long time.

2014
01:16:14,336 --> 01:16:19,107
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
